Now, This fort has become a museum.In a number of buildings inside this fort there are dioramas about Indonesian history.

The De Mata Museum is one of the museums that contains the most 3D paintings in the world. There are around 120 paintings in total and each painting has a concept with a realistic looking background. There are several sizes of paintings in the De Mata Museum, from the usual size to up to 5 meters. There are several categories of his paintings, namely ornaments, landscapes, sports, famous figures, superheroes, to circus paintings. This museum was established for the public to spend their holidays by gaining knowledge. This museum offers many unique paintings, for example there are paintings where you can feel the excitement of walking on a wooden bridge under which there is a steep ravine or struggling to extinguish the hot flames from the dragon's mouth, these paintings look as if they were real. All of that is contained in the De Mata museum with effects that deceive the eye.

Taman Sari Yogyakarta or Taman Sari Keraton Yogyakarta (Hanacaraka:ˆ? ˆ??ˆ??ˆ??ˆ?ñˆ?®ˆ??ˆ??ˆ?¦ˆ?§ˆ??ˆ?'ˆ??ˆ? ˆ? ?ˆ?­, Tamansari Ngayogyakarta) is the site of a former palace garden or garden of the Keraton Ngayogyakarta Hadiningrat, which can be compared to the Bogor Botanical Gardens as the gardens of the Bogor Palace. This garden was built during the time of Sultan Hamengku Buwono I (HB I) in 1758-1765/9. Initially, the park which received the title "The Fragrant Garden" has an area of more than 10 hectares with around 57 buildings in the form of buildings, bathing pools, suspension bridges, water canals, as well as artificial lakes along with artificial islands and underwater passages. The garden, which was used effectively between 1765-1812, originally stretched from the southwest of the Kedhaton complex to the southeast of the Magangan complex. However, at present, the only remnants of Taman Sari that can be seen are in the southwest of the Kedhaton complex.

The Warungboto site or Pesanggrahan Rejawinangun is a cultural heritage building located at Jalan Veteran No.77, Warungboto Village, Umbulharjo District, Yogyakarta City, Yogyakarta Special Region. Initially, this site was the location of a guest house and baths.

Even though it is just an intersection, the Point 0 km intersection is not an ordinary intersection. Because at this intersection you can say that it is the center point of the city of Jogja because of its location which is actually in front of the Yogyakarta Palace as the founder of this special area. What's more, to the north is the center of Jogja's tourist crowd, namely Jalan Malioboro, so if you are hanging out at the Zero Kilometer Point intersection, you will really feel the center point of Jogja which is so serene. Point 0 Yogyakarta Yogyakarta is indeed a favorite place for tourists to spend time, especially in the afternoon and evening which are always crowded every day with tourists who just hang out on the many seats provided around the intersection.

Gembira Loka Zoo is commonly called Gembira Loka Zoo (abbreviated GL Zoo, Javanese: ˆ? ˆ?¬ˆ??ˆ?§ˆ??ˆ??ˆ??ƒ??ˆ?®ˆ??ƒ??ˆ?' ˆ?¬ˆ??ˆ??ˆ??ˆ??ˆ?®ƒ??ˆ?ˆ?§ˆ??ˆ? , translit. Raja G¦mbira Loka) is a zoo located in Yogyakarta City. Contains various species from around the world, such as orangutans, Asian elephants, chimpanzees, tigers, and so on. Gembira Loka Zoo is a special attraction for Yogyakarta tourists. Gembira Loka Zoo was severely damaged due to the Yogyakarta earthquake in 2006. However, after being renovated, Gembira Loka Zoo is still sought after by tourists.
Sumur Gumuling is one of the places for worship or religious activities in the past. Sumur Gumuling was a mosque during the reign of Sri Sultan Hamengkubuwana I and II.

Place_Name: Code River Tourism Village Jogja City
Description: Kampung Code is located in Kotabaru Village, Gondokusuman District, Yogyakarta City. The exact location is RT 01/RW 01 to the south of the Gondolayu bridge on Jl Jenderal Sudirman or to the east of the Kali Code riverbank which divides the city of Yogyakarta. Kampung Code is located right on the banks of the Code River which extends to the south with a contour of cliffs from top to bottom. At the top, which is close to Jl. Faridan M. Noto, most of the residents use it for the service business/buying and selling of car tires. While at the bottom is a residential area. Kampung Code, which was once an ordinary village, has been transformed into a work of art thanks to the services of an architect and Catholic religious leader, Father YB Manguwijaya.

Alun-alun Selatan or what is now better known as Alun-alun Kidul (Alkid) is the main square which is located south of the Yogyakarta Palace. This square is in the form of a wide sandy field, with an area of about 160m x 160m. This square is surrounded by a brick wall with a height of 2.20 m, the thickness of the wall is 30 cm. Many have collapsed and been damaged. The wall fence that can be seen now is the new wall fence, which was built by Sri Sultan Hamengkubuwono VII during his reign in 1877 -1921 AD.

Yogya Kembali Monument Museum (Javanese: ˆ??ˆ?§ˆ??ˆ??ˆ??ˆ??ˆ?§ˆ??ˆ??ƒ??ˆ?¦ˆ?§ˆ??ˆ?'ˆ??ƒ? ?ˆ? ˆ?¬ˆ??ˆ??ˆ??ˆ?ˆ??, translit. Monum??n Yogya Lagi) commonly known as the Jogja Lagi Monument, abbreviated as Monjali, is a history museum of the struggle for Indonesian independence in the Special Region of Yogyakarta and managed by the Ministry of Tourism and Creative Economy. The museum, which is located in the northern part of the city, is visited by many students on field trips.\n\nThis cone-shaped monument museum consists of 3 floors and is equipped with a library and multipurpose room. On the entrance gate, the names of 422 heroes who died in the Wehrkreise III (RIS) area were written between 19 December 1948 and 29 June 1949. In the 4 rooms of the museum on the 1st floor, there are collections of objects: reliefs, replicas, photographs, documents, heraldry, various types of weapons, evocative forms of public kitchens in the atmosphere of the war for independence 1945-1949. Stretchers and carriages (horse carriages) that were once used by the Commander-in-Chief General Soedirman are also stored here (in museum room number 2). Yogya Lagi Monument is located at Jl. North Ring Road, Sleman Regency, Special Region of Yogyakarta.

Taman Pelangi Yogyakarta is a night tourist spot that displays colorful lantern lights, so it looks like a rainbow. This tourist park is located on Jalan Padjajaran (formerly known as Jalan Ring Road Utara), and is in the location of the Yogya Kembali Monument Museum (Monumen Jogja Kembali) Yogyakarta. Taman Pelangi has more than 20 types of games, 25 food stands and drink stands. This rainbow park can be enjoyed from evening to night, or from 17.00 to 23.00. Your evening will feel complete and perfect in Taman Pelangi with lots of lit lanterns giving an interesting impression to calm your mind.

Regionally, the Duchy Tourism Village is located in the Duchy Village, Kraton District. Its existence also functions as a buffer for the Yogyakarta Sultanate Palace tourism object. In accordance with the existing potential, the Kadipaten Tourism Village then adopted the theme "Art and Heritage Tourism" as its branding. This tourist village area is very unique and specific because there are many cultural heritage site buildings, especially the Dalem Prince building. The name of the Duchy itself is said to have come from the name of the area where there are many cultural heritage sites, especially the Dalem Prince building. The name of the Kadipaten is said to have come from the name of the area where many relatives of the Kraton lived there who were also the exalters of the Kraton.

Yogyakarta Cultural Park (TBY) (Hanacaraka:ˆ? ˆ??ˆ??ˆ??ƒ??ˆ??ˆ??ˆ?›ˆ?¦ƒ??ˆ??ˆ?¦ˆ?§ˆ??ˆ?' ˆ??ˆ? ˆ??ˆ?, Javanese: Taman Budaya Ngayogyakarta) is a tourist facility located at Jalan Sri Wedani No 1, Yogyakarta. TBY has a building complex that functions as a venue for exhibitions, performances and various other artistic activities. TBY is the Service Technical Implementation Unit (UPTD) at the Department of Culture of the Special Province of Yogyakarta. The function of TBY is as a cultural center including the development and processing of documentation centers, display cases, and information on cultural arts and tourism.

Sosromenduran tourist village is a very unique tourist village because it is based on multi-culture, accommodation and shopping as well as functioning as a buffer for the Malioboro Tourism Object area. Regionally, the Sosromenduran tourism village is located in the Sosromenduran Village, Gedongtengen District. Its location is very strategic because it is located next to the Malioboro area and is also very close to the Tugu Train Station and there are many tourism facilities, both hotels, homestays, stalls and restaurants, travel, money changers, coffee, car rental, motorbikes and even ontel bicycles and what is very interesting in Sosromenduran tourism village also has many T-shirt souvenir manufacturers which are also sold along Jalan Malioboro

The government's attention to batik culture is very large, this is because the culture is in direct contact with the Javanese people. Commemorating National Batik Day today, travelers can take a walk to the batik monuments in Jogja. The government's attention to batik culture is very large, this is because the culture is in direct contact with the Javanese people. Commemorating National Batik Day today, travelers can take a walk to the batik monuments in Jogja.

Tugu Yogyakarta (Javanese: , Tugu Ngayogyakarta) is an important historical landmark in the city of Yogyakarta, Indonesia. Tugu means monument, which is usually built as a symbol of an area that conceptualizes the characteristics of that area. Due to its historical background, Tugu Yogyakarta has become a historical icon of the city. Tugu Yogyakarta is located right in the middle of the intersection between Jalan Mangkubumi, Jalan Sudirman, Jalan AM Sangaji, and Jalan Dipenogoro kota.

Breksi Cliff is a tourist spot in the Sleman Regency area. The location is south of Prambanan Temple and close to Ijo Temple and Boko Palace Complex. The Breksi Cliff Tourism location is precisely in Sambirejo Village, Prambanan, Sleman Regency, Special Region of Yogyakarta 55572.

Although attached to the word temple, Donotirto Temple is not a relic from the Hindu-Buddhist era in Yogyakarta. This place was built by the Dutch government. There are two parts, namely the western part for men and the east for women. Each of them is fed by 5 showers of water sourced from the Winogo River, meaning there are 10 showers there. Until now, this place is still being cared for by local residents even though it is used as a public toilet. Therefore, don't be heavy-handed to set aside your money in exchange for maintenance and cleaning costs for this place.

Jalan Malioboro is the name of one of the three streets in the city of Yogyakarta that stretches from Tugu Yogyakarta to the Yogyakarta Post Office intersection. Overall it consists of Jalan Margo Utomo, Jalan Malioboro, and Jalan Margo Mulyo. This road is the axis of the Yogyakarta Kraton Imaginary Line.

The main building is the Performance Ward which was formerly known as Tratag Rambat. In his era, Pagelaran was the place where the royal officials met the Sultan for official ceremonies. Now it is often used for tourism, religious, and other events in addition to traditional palace ceremonies. A pair of Pemandangan Wards are located on the far east and west side of Pagelaran. Formerly this place was used by the Sultan to watch war games at Lor Alun-alun.

Embung or Tambakboyo Reservoir is a water conservation area located in Tambakboyo Hamlet, Depok District, Sleman Regency, Yogyakarta. This reservoir utilizes water sources from the Tambak Bayan and Buntung rivers with an area of 7.8 ha. This reservoir was built from 2003 to 2008 and was inaugurated a year later.

Pengger Pine Forest (Javanese: ˆ??ˆ?ˆ?ñˆ??ƒ??ˆ?ˆ??ˆ??ˆ??ˆ?ñ???ƒ??ˆ?ˆ?¬ˆ? ƒ ??ˆ?'ˆ?¬ˆ??ƒ??, translit. Alas Pinusƒ?? PŽ?nggŽ?r) is one of the mainstay tourist attractions in Bantul Regency. This natural tourism is located in Sendangsari, Eggplant Village, Kec. Dlingo, Bantul Regency, Special Region of Yogyakarta. \nThe Pengger Pine Forest is easy to reach because it is located on the side of the Patuk-Dlingo km 4.5 road. \nAlthough it still sounds foreign, among those who like touring tourist attractions, the Pengger Pine Forest is quite popular. This place still feels foreign because it was only officially opened on April 7 2016. This pine forest is very popular with tourist attraction creators, because this tourist attraction offers very beautiful natural scenery.

The Serangan General March 1 Monument is located in the area around the Fort Vredeburg Museum, which is right in front of the Yogyakarta Post Office. This monument was built to commemorate the Indonesian army's attack on the Netherlands on March 1, 1949. At that time the Indonesian State was considered paralyzed and did not exist by the Dutch. To prove that the State of Indonesia still exists, a massive attack was carried out. This attack was carried out by the Indonesian National Armed Forces (TNI) led by Lieutenant Colonel Suharto, Commander of the 10th Brigade Wehrkreise III area.

Pinus Becici Peak or Becici Peak is a tourist attraction located in Muntuk Village, Dlingo District, Bantul Regency, Yogyakarta. The scenery in this area is very beautiful with a stretch of hills that are overgrown with pine trees and you can see the charm of the city of Yogyakarta from a height with a viewing post. From the north you can see Prambanan Temple, from the south you can see a straight line which is the South Beach and you can see Mount Merapi and Mount Sindoro.

Bukit Bintang is one of the favorite hangout locations in Yogyakarta. When night falls, the view of Yogyakarta is very beautiful! Located on the border of Bantul and Gunungkidul, anyone who visits this area can enjoy the stars in the night sky and the bright city lights twinkling from a height. This city has Bukit Bintang which is always busy with young people. enjoy the beauty of the night. Bukit Bintang is the perfect place to enjoy dusk until nightfall.

The Yogyakarta palace, known as Gedung Agung (Javanese: ˆ?'ˆ?¬ˆ? ˆ?§ˆ??ˆ? ƒ??ˆ??ˆ?'ˆ?¬ˆ? , translit. Gedhong Ageng) is located in the center of the bustling city , precisely at the southern end of Jalan Ahmad Yani, formerly known as Jalan Margomulyo. The palace area is located in Ngupasan Village, Gondomanan District, Yogyakarta City, and is located at an altitude of 120 m above sea level. This palace complex occupies an area of 43,585 mý.

The Lost World Castle is a tourist attraction on the slopes of Mount Merapi, located in Petung Hamlet, Kepuharjo Cangkringan Village, Sleman, Special Region of Yogyakarta, Indonesia. This tourist attraction was built to resemble Fort Takeshi and was built on 1.3 hectares of land in 2016. Visitors who wish to enter The Lost World Castle area will be charged a fee of IDR 25,000 per person and does not include parking fees. The parking fee for a car is IDR 5,000.00, while the parking fee for motorbikes is IDR 2,000.00.

The Sanapati Monument was built to commemorate 50 years of Indonesian coding in Yogyakarta. Coding in Yogyakarta has played a big role in maintaining the independence of the State of Indonesia. It was recorded that during the March 1, 1949 General Attack, the code created by Roebiono was still used to spread a message to the world that Indonesia still existed and could still fight. Subsequently, this event became known as the 6 Hours Incident in Yogyakarta. The Sanapati Monument is located in the Kotabaru area, in the middle of the intersection of Jalan Abu Bakar Ali, in the front garden of St. Anthony's Church. The Sanapati Monument building has a triangular shape with sharp ends resembling a pyramid with a height of 3 meters and a width of 2.5 meters. The monument was designed by Drs Kasman and inaugurated by the Minister of State Secretary of the Republic of Indonesia at that time, Moerdiono, on April 4 1996, on Indonesian Encryption Day. The construction of the monument takes one month and costs 25 million rupiah.

The Tembelan Kanigoro Gorge is located in the Mangunan Tourism Village, Dlingo, Bantul. Familiar with Mangunan Village, right? This area does have good tourist attractions that are cheap. Including the Tembelan Kanigoro Gorge which is not far from the Mangunan Orchard or Panguk Kediwung Hill. From Jogja, direct the vehicle to Jalan Imogiri Timur, after arriving at the T-junction near Imogiri Market, follow the direction towards Mangunan. To get there, first check the condition of the vehicle. Roads that go up and down and sharp turns, you have to watch out for. For those who use large vehicles such as buses, it is hoped that they will go around Bukit Bintang Gunung Kidul. In addition, always be careful and stay focused while driving.

Place_Name: The World Landmarks - Merapi Park Yogyakarta
Description: Merapi Park is one of the tourist attractions in Yogyakarta which is located on Jalan Kaliurang km 22, Hargobinangun, Pakem District, Sleman Regency. Operation of Merapi Park began on June 25 2017. The facilities available include a place to take photos

The Sonobudoyo Museum is a museum and library of Javanese history and culture in Yogyakarta, Indonesia. This museum contains the most complete collection of Javanese artefacts, after the National Museum in Jakarta. In addition to Neolithic era ceramics and 8th century bronze statues, the museum also houses a collection of wayang, various ancient weapons (such as keris), and Javanese masks. The Sonobudoyo Museum consists of two units, Unit I is located at Jalan Trikora No. 6 Yogyakarta, and Unit II is located in Ndalem Condrokiranan, Wijilan, east of the main square (north) of the city.

The DIY region offers a number of tourism potentials, especially river-based tourism. One of them which is now one of the favorites of tourists is the Lava Pillow which is in Berbah District, Sleman Regency. As the name implies, this tourist attraction offers rocks that are thought to have originated from incandescent lava from underwater volcanoes that dried up hundreds of years ago. Lying on the Opak River, these rocks are a unique sight that can catch the attention of travelers. It is said that the existence of Pillow Lava contributed greatly to the formation of Java Island. Natural phenomena like what happened in the Pillow Lava are very rare. On the island of Java, a similar phenomenon can only be found in Karanggulung (Kebumen), Ciletuh (West Java), and in Berbah (DIY). Against the background of a long geological history, since October 2, 2014, the government has designated this tourist attraction as a geo heritage. This means that all the geological uniqueness in the tourist object is classified as an object protected by the government.

Panguk Kediwung Hill is a tourist attraction that offers natural views from a height. When compared to other hilly tourism objects in Bantul, Panguk Kediwung Hill is indeed relatively new because it opened in 2016. But make no mistake, this location has stolen the hearts of many visitors from within and outside the city. Panguk Kediwung Hill is located in Kediwung, Mangunan, Dlingo, Bantul, Yogyakarta. Don't worry about getting lost because along the way to the location we will see some signposts. Approximately 20 km from the center of Yogyakarta City. From the center of Yogyakarta City, you can head south to Jalan Imogiri Timur, follow the road until you find Imogiri Market, then turn left and continue your journey towards Dlingo, from there you will see directions to Panguk Kediwung Hill. The access road to Panguk Kediwung Hill has been smoothly paved, it's just that the contours go up and down slightly but are still in the safe category. It is highly recommended to use a private vehicle because access here using public transportation is quite difficult.

Prambanan Temple or Roro Jonggrang Temple (Javanese: ˆ??ˆ??ˆ??ˆ? ˆ??ƒ??ˆ?ˆ?¨ˆ??ˆ??ˆ??ˆ??ˆ??ˆ? ?, translit. Candi Prambanan) is the largest Hindu temple complex in Indonesia which was built in the 9th century AD. This temple is dedicated to Trimurti, the three main Hindu gods namely Brahma as the creator god, Vishnu as the guardian god, and Shiva as the god of destruction. Based on the Siwagrha inscription, the original name of this temple complex is Siwagrha (Sanskrit which means 'House of Shiva'). nThe whole Prambanan temple complex is located in the province of the Special Region of Yogyakarta, but its administrative doors are in the Special Region of Surakarta (now part of Central Java Province), this makes Prambanan Temple located in 2 places, namely in Bokoharjo Village, Prambanan District, Sleman Regency , and in Tlogo Village, Prambanan District, Klaten Regency, or approximately 17 kilometers northeast of Yogyakarta, 50 kilometers southwest of Surakarta and 120 kilometers south of Semarang, right on the border between the Special Region of Yogyakarta and the Special Region of Surakarta. This temple is a Heritage Site. UNESCO world, the largest Hindu temple in Indonesia, as well as one of the most beautiful temples in Southeast Asia. The architecture of this building is tall and slender in accordance with Hindu architecture in general with the Shiva temple as the main temple having a height of up to 47 meters rising in the middle of a complex of clusters of smaller temples. As one of the grandest temples in Southeast Asia, the Prambanan temple attracts tourists from all over the world. According to the Siwagrha inscription, this temple was built around 850 AD by Rakai Pikatan, and continued to be developed and expanded by Balitung Maha Sambu, during the royal period. Medang Mataram.

Watu Goyang comes from the Javanese language which means rocking rock. Previously, in this place there was a rock at the top that could sway when touched or pushed. The stone has been around for hundreds of years. The managers explained that Watu Goyang never collapsed even though it was touched and even climbed, but the manager forbade visitors who try to climb the Watu Goyang because it would be very dangerous for safety. The uniqueness of this giant stone is its structure which contains unique protrusions. The natural landscape is still green and the volcano looks very natural, very suitable for visitors to get rid of boredom with daily activities in urban areas. Being at this peak visitors will feel the cool air temperature, especially in the morning. And during the day, even though the weather is hot, the breeze that greets feels fresh and comfortable.

The Rejowinangun tourist village is located in Rejowinangun Village, Kotagede District, Yogyakarta City, to be precise, south of the Gembiraloka Zoo. This tourist village has been initiated since 2010 and with the cooperation of all elements of society, on October 4, 2013 by the Head of the Yogyakarta City Tourism Office, the Rejowinangun Tourism Village was inaugurated. Rejowinangun Sub-District is one of three sub-districts in Kotagede District, a sub-district at the eastern end of Yogyakarta City which is famous for its silver and was the former kingdom of Mataram. Kelurahan Rejowinangun has a lot of potential which, if developed, would be extraordinary, even though at the moment what is well-known is the Gembiraloka Botanical Garden (KRKB) which is located in the Kelurahan Rejowinangun area. With the KRKB Gembiraloka tourist spot in this area, trying to develop the sub-district area with the existing potential so that tourists besides visiting Gembiraloka can stop at this tourist village.

Pakualaman is a sub-district in the City of Yogyakarta, Province of the Special Region of Yogyakarta, Indonesia. This sub-district is located between the Code River and the Manunggal River. The name 'Pakualaman' is taken from Puro Paku Alaman, the official residence of Sri Paduka Pakualam which is located right in the middle of this sub-district. Previously, Pakualaman was not part of Yogyakarta city, but Pakualaman City District, which was abolished after the formation of the Yogyakarta City Government in 1947.

Alun-alun Utara or in Javanese it is called Alun-alun Lor is one of the landmarks of the City of Yogyakarta in the form of a field in front of the Yogyakarta Palace. It is called Alun-alun Lor because in the city of Yogyakarta there are two squares which are located to the south and north of the Yogyakarta Palace. Alun-alun Lor is a square with an area of 150 x 150 meters with two large fenced banyan trees in the middle of the square. The two large banyan trees are each named Kyai Dewandaru and Kyai Wijayandaru. In the past, 63 banyan trees were planted around Lor Square, which symbolized the age of the Prophet Muhammad SAW.

Goa Cemara Beach (Javanese: ˆ?ˆ?ñˆ??ˆ?ñˆ??ˆ??ƒ?? ˆ?'ˆ??ˆ??ƒ?? ˆ??ˆ?§ˆ??ˆ? ®, translit. Pasisir Guwa Cemaraƒ??) is a beach tourism object located in Patihan Hamlet, Gadingsari Village, Sanden District, Bantul Regency. Special Region of Yogyakarta. This beach is located right side by side with Samas Beach and Pandansari Beach. This beach has black but soft sand with quite large waves characteristic of the south coast. This beach is a new development beach where there are many shady pine trees forming a cave, this is what makes this beach named Goa Cemara. This fir tree aims to protect sea water abrasion and prevent sand dunes from experiencing displacement due to wind.

Blue Lagoon is one of Jogja's famous water attractions and is visited by many tourists from all over the world. Many think that the Blue Lagoon is a hidden Jogja tourist paradise. Even though the beauty offered by this place is very expensive, to be able to enjoy it you don't need to spend deeply. Because the budget to enter this tourist area is not as expensive as in Iceland.

Parangkusumo Sand Dunes (Javanese: ˆ?'ˆ??ˆ??ˆ??ˆ? ˆ??ƒ??ˆ?ˆ?ñˆ??ˆ??ƒ??ˆ?ˆ?®ˆ? ƒ??ˆ? ˆ??ˆ?ñˆ??ˆ??, translit. Sand Gumuk Parangkusuma) is a tourist attraction in Bantul Regency, Yogyakarta, located to the west of Parangtritis Beach, namely in Parangtritis Village, Kretek District, Bantul Regency , Special Region of Yogyakarta. This sand dune has a number of features related to its limited number in the world. The name "gumuk" comes from the Javanese language which means wide expanse of sand dunes. The Yogyakarta Sand Dunes are formed from Mount Merapi material which then undergoes transportation via the Opak River and the Progo River which are then carried by the waves and settle on the beach. The material that settles then dries and is carried by the wind and then flies ashore so that it undergoes a deposition process to become Sand Dunes.

Lintang Sewu Hill originates when at night on this hill you can see thousands of stars stretching across the sky. In Javanese, Bukit Seribu Bintang is Bukit Lintang Sewu (latitude: star, sewu: one thousand). Natural scenery that is no less enchanting makes Bukit Langit Sewu a favorite place for nature lovers. When heading to the hill, visitors will be presented with pine trees, but when they arrive they will be presented with a panoramic view of the Eucalyptus forest which is the uniqueness of this tourist spot. Above this Eucalyptus tree there is also a Kestrel bird that passes above the tree. Besides that, visitors will also be spoiled by a row of mountains such as Mount Merbabu, Mount Sumbing, Menoreh, and Mount Merapi.

Studio Gamplong or Studio Alam Gamplong is a tourist spot located in Gamplong Village, Moyudan District, Sleman Regency. This place was originally the shooting location for the film Sultan Agung: Throne, Struggle, Love and Earth of Mankind by Hanung Bramantyo. The place was built on an area of 2.5 hectares. The place was inaugurated by President Joko Widodo on 15 July 2018.

The location of the Watu Lumbung Educational Village, which is in a hilly area filled with teak tree groves, makes the view from this place very beautiful. Watu Lumbung was conceptualized by M Boy Rifai as a place that teaches educational values, where Boy Rifai has succeeded in conjuring a barren land that was previously left alone, now becoming an exotic place to enjoy the night and see the sunset and sunrise. To maintain the beauty of the area around tourist attractions, the management deliberately built this area as a tourist area that is in harmony with nature.

Kedung Pedut Waterfall or commonly called Kedung Pedut Waterfall comes from a Javanese term. Curug means waterfall, kedung means puddle or pond, and pedut means fog. Kedung Pedut Waterfall is one of the natural attractions in Kulonprogo which is known for its beautiful water color.

Place_Name: The peak of the Mangunan Orchard
Description: Vacationing in the mountains is fun. Can enjoy the cool air and beautiful views from the top of the hills. Tourism like this can be enjoyed in Bantul, precisely at the Mangunan Fruit Farm. Luckily Jogja is blessed with such beautiful landscapes. There are beaches, mountains, hills, and very interesting cities and culture. Mangunan Fruit Garden is present as a tourist attraction that attracts tourists. Especially in the morning, the view is like the land above the clouds.

Gamplong Tourism Village is a weaving craft tourism village located in Padukuhan Gamplong, Sumber Rahayu Village, Moyudan District, Sleman Regency, Yogyakarta. This tourist village which is located to the west of the city of Yogyakarta is quite interesting for tourists to stop by, especially because there is still a traditional weaving craft industry using Non-Machine Weaving Tools (ATBM). With ATBM, the Gamplong artisan community is able to produce woven cloth as stagen material (a long cloth to wrap around a woman's abdomen). In addition to woven crafts, craftsmen are also able to produce woven crafts for souvenirs.

Sosrowijayan tourist spot has indeed been known as Kampung Caucasian Tourism, the location itself is in the center of Yogyakarta city so that almost every day at this location there are lots of very dense visitors. For those of you who want to visit here, you have to use a vehicle because from the direction of Tugu station you just have to walk for 200 meters and then you will immediately find the Sosrowijayan area which has a sign, namely A Small Road to the West with the same name. Sosrowijayan's unique tour divides into two areas, namely Sosrowijayan Wetan and Sosrowijayan Kulon and connects Jalan Jogonegaran and Jalan Malioboro. However, Sosrowijayan Wetan is currently well-known all over the world and is known as the second tourist village in Yogyakarta after Prawirotaman. Because it is called Kampung Caucasians, even here you will see lots of tourists from abroad enjoying the night atmosphere in Yogyakarta. You can also see two rotten fruit like those in the Prawirotaman area when you enter the first dan. In this area, there are lots of books for sale, such as English novels, Indonesian booklets, and several quality books that will certainly provide education for their readers.

That tourist object is not Grojogan Watu Purbo which is in Bangunrejo, Merdikorejo, Tempel District. This tourist attraction in the last year has been quite popular among tourists because it has an exotic view of a waterfall which has six levels. Tourists who come on average use the waterfall as a backdrop for selfies because the view is considered instagramable. Grojokan Watu Purbo is precisely located on the Krisak River, which is the path of cold lava flowing from Mount Merapi. The view of this area is exotic because it is surrounded by beautiful trees and expanses of rice fields. The emergence of this waterfall or grojogan comes from six dams with varying heights of no more than 10 meters.

Kalibiru is actually the name of a forest which is currently being processed into a natural tourist spot. Kalibiru Forest has a height of 450 meters above sea level and is in the form of a fertile hill area. The air temperature in this place is very cool. Kalibiru is managed by the government and the local community as nature and educational tourism. There are many things that can be found there, including outbound, lodging, and several spots to find contemporary photos. There are also trekking routes which can also be used as camping locations.

In Yogyakarta, in Sleman to be precise, there is an educational tourist spot that is worth a visit. Its name is Jogja Exotarium ? sounds unique, right? But actually, this place is a small-scale animal park. The collection of animals is diverse and can be directly interacted with

Place_Name: Peak of the Ancient Volcano - Nglanggeran
Description: Mount Nglanggeran is a mountain in the Special Region of Yogyakarta, Indonesia. This mountain is an ancient volcano that was formed around 0.6-70 million years ago or has a tertiary age (Oligo-Miocene). Mount Nglanggeran has very distinctive rocks because it is dominated by volcanic agglomerates and breccias. This mountain is located in Nglanggeran Village, Patuk District, Gunung Kidul Regency which is in the Baturagung Mountains row.

The Lepen weir itself used to be an irrigation canal that was not as clean as it is today. Previously, this place was a rundown irrigation canal accompanied by an abandoned village garden. However, the youth's awareness of environmental cleanliness has turned the river (river/lepen) which was originally so dirty into a tourist spot that is liked by many people. The Lepen weir is now beautiful and filled with tilapia and carp. If previously it was just an abandoned and rundown tourist park, now Lepen Dam is a comfortable tourist destination to visit with family. Even during the COVID-19 pandemic, the Lepen Dam has no shortage of enthusiasts. There are still many children who enjoy the twilight happily while feeding the fish in the river. Of course accompanied by their parents who can also wash their eyes seeing the clear flow of water with colorful fish swimming in the river. Apart from that, there are also many young people sitting in the garden while enjoying the cool afternoon air accompanied by a glass of iced tea.

Kaliadem Bunker is a tourist attraction located on the southern slope of Mount Merapi. This tourist destination has many traces of the volcanic eruption, especially in 2006 and 2010. This phenomenal location is located at an altitude of more than 2,000 meters above sea level. Located in Sleman Regency, tourists are invited to witness the majesty of Merapi from a distance of five kilometers. This area combines the history, beauty and natural uniqueness of Mount Merapi with its volcanic phenomena.

The Ledok Sambi tourist village is a village that has a natural feel of Jogja, which is located close to Mount Merapi or is located on Jl. Kaliurang Km. 19.2 Padukuhan Sambi Desa Pakembinangun Kec. Pakem Sleman Regency Special Region of Yogyakarta. Beautiful natural scenery can provide coolness, freshness and peace of mind. As far as the eye can see in this tourist village you will be presented with a wide expanse of natural and beautiful rice fields and also shady green trees and clear water that belongs to the Ledok Sambi Tourism Village area. The spacious traditional houses of Jogja are used as a place to play while enjoying the cool air that soothes the heart, soul and mind.

The name One Thousand Stones Songgo Langit has its own meaning. Before it became a tourist spot, in this location there were hundreds or even thousands of rocks and of course a pine forest. Songgo Langit means support for the sky, this is because in Seribu Baru Songgo Langit there is a hill that seems to be a pillar of the sky. Seribu Batu Songgo Langit is a tourist spot in the Dlingo area that offers various kinds of tourist attractions, but most of them are photo spots. Almost all of the photo spots at Seribu Batu are anti-mainstream. You will find several photo spots in four parts at this tourist spot. Entering the Seribu Batu Songgo Langit gate, you are required to go down a wooden ladder to reach the first spot. This first spot offers a fairytale thousand-wood house. This spot is in the form of a small house that resembles a dwarf's house in a fairy tale. There are seven dwarves' houses that are arranged in a conical manner so that they will create a good photo angle.

Jomblang Cave is a vertical collapse doline type cave. This cave was formed due to the geological process of the collapse of the soil and the vegetation on it to the bottom of the earth that occurred thousands of years ago. This collapse forms a sinkhole or well which in Javanese is known as luweng. That is what makes it unique because inside the cave there is an area of the mouth of the cave about 50 meters. It is often called Luweng Jomblang. Jomblang Cave is located in Gunungkidul Regency, DI Yogyakarta. Currently, Jomblang Cave is a place for ancient plant conservation and has been developed into a special interest tourist spot which is managed by residents or local residents. To descend into this vertical cave, the management has provided complete equipment according to caving safety standards in vertical caves. The sunlight that penetrates from Luweng Grubug as high as 90 meters forms a pillar of light, illuminating the beautiful flowstone and the depths of the pitch-dark cave. Water dripping from a height also beautifies the view. It's not wrong if many people come here in awe when they see the natural painting known as "heavenly light".

The Teletubbies village area has attracted attention from various media, so tourists have started to flock there. Until now, this area has become a unique Jogja tourist attraction that is interesting to visit. For datatour friends who are on vacation or domiciled in Yogyakarta and around, try to experience this unique tourism sensation, at least it can be used as a photo collection that carries cool instagenic spots. At first the Rumah Domes tourist attraction was a form of assistance from an NGO, at that time Yogyakarta was hit by an earthquake natural disaster. In Nglepen village there are at least 80 buildings carrying the complete dome house design along with facilities such as food stalls, public toilets, parking areas, places of worship, health houses and village halls which are often used when there are celebrations or cultural events. This Sumberharjo tourist village has an area of approximately 2 hectares and the building was built since 2006. Apart from being called the Teletubbies village, the settlement there is also often called New Nglepen.

Pule Payung Yogyakarta. A popular tourist attraction that presents natural beauty from a height of 500 meters above sea level. Bukit Wisata Pule Payung Yogyakarta is a tourist area filled with high creativity, changing ordinary zones into extraordinary ones. The first attraction of Pule Payung Yogyakarta is a tourist attraction that presents the natural charm of the mountains. So, people call it Bukit Wisata. The height of Pule Payung Yogyakarta is around 500 meters above sea level, and the road to Pule Payung Yogyakarta can be reached by two-wheeled or four-wheeled vehicles. The charm of the beauty of the Sermo Reservoir can be seen clearly while in Pule Payung. Exotic reservoir surrounded by mountains that are still beautiful. And Pule Payung Yogyakarta is a hill which incidentally is a natural tourist destination, given a touch of creativity, and prioritizing safety aspects at each spot, eventually becoming a favorite tour in Jogja.

Bentara Budaya Yogyakarta is a cultural center located in Yogyakarta, Indonesia. Bentara Budaya Yogyakarta opened on 26 September 1982, funded by Kompas Gramedia Group. Bentara Budaya Yogyakarta is a branch of Bentara Budaya Jakarta, a cultural institution managed by Kompas Gramedia Group which also has several cultural centers in Jakarta, Surakarta (as Balai Soedjatmoko), and Bali.

Rancang Kencono Cave, located in Padukuhan Menggoran, Bleberan Village, Playen District, Gunungkidul, Yogyakarta, is one of the caves inhabited by prehistoric to modern humans. It is estimated that the cave which is located in the Sri Getuk waterfall area has been inhabited since 3000 years ago. From the book Variety of Cultural Heritage and Cultural Heritage of Gunungkidul written by Winarsih (Head of Archaeology and Museums Section, Preservation of Cultural Heritage and Cultural Values, Gunungkidul Cultural Office), Archeology UGM Yogyakarta in 2001 has already conducted this research. Rancang Kencono Cave has been inhabited by humans since 3000 years ago with evidence of findings of human bones.

Cerme Cave (Javanese: ˆ?'ˆ??ˆ??ƒ??ˆ??ˆ?§ˆ??ˆ??ˆ?§, translit. Cerme Cave) is a historic cave and at the same time a tourist spot located in Srunggo Hamlet , Selopamioro Village, Imogiri District, Bantul Regency or about 20 km south of Yogyakarta City. Cerme Cave has a length of 1.5 km which penetrates to spring in the Panggang area, namely in Ploso Hamlet, Giritirto Village, Purwosari District, Gunungkidul Regency. Besides Cerme Cave, there are other smaller caves around it such as Goa Dalang, Goa Ledek , Clown Cave and Kaum Cave which are often used for meditation. To reach the cave, there are stairs as high as 759 m. The word cerme comes from the word lecture which indicates the discussion conducted by the walisongo. Cerme Cave was once used by the Walisongos to spread Islam in Java. Apart from that, the Cerme Cave is also used to discuss plans to build the Great Mosque of Demak. Every Monday or Tuesday, a thanksgiving ceremony is always held to ask God for blessings.

Kraton Jogja is a royal complex that stands right in the middle of the city of Yogyakarta. The palace, which was founded in line with the Giyanti agreement in 1755 which split the Islamic Mataram Kingdom into the Ngayogyakarta Surakarta Kingdom, has the undoubted beauty of Javanese architecture, and is one of the best palace complexes in Java. The beauty of the Jogja Palace is inseparable from its founder, namely Sri Sultan Hamengkubuwono I who is the architect of this kingdom. If you are on a tour to the Kraton Jogja, if you come from Malioboro Street, you will first be greeted by the Pangurakan Gate, which has a thick Javanese architecture, which is adjacent to the Dutch East Indies buildings. After entering it you will enter the North Square which has a fairly large area. Around it there are closed joglos called Gedhong and open joglos called Tratag. In this area there are several culinary options that are perfect for you to visit before you enter the Yogyakarta Kraton complex, so you don't feel hungry.

Kelor tourism village is one of the villages in Sleman district which is currently being developed into a tourist village. This Kelor tourist village offers a rural atmosphere where the residents make a living as farmers, ranchers, and mushroom cultivation. Lots of greenery that stretches wide with beautiful natural scenery. This Kelor tourist village has a friendly community and has a very comfortable village environment. Kelor Village also has a river, and the water in the river is still clear and beautiful.
This beach is located in the Srigading, Sanden area and is quite close to Goa Cemara Beach. The place is also really fun for taking photos, not much different from Pandasari.

Kukup Beach is a beach that has a stretch of white sand which is famous in Gunung Kidul Regency, Yogyakarta. Besides having a beautiful beach view, this beach also provides its own uniqueness. On this beach there is a coral island which is the main attraction for local and foreign tourists. Because on this coral island tourists can enjoy the beauty of a very charming beach. This beautiful beach is located to the east of Baron Beach, approximately 1 km away. Precisely located in Kemadang Village, Tanjungsari District, Gunung Kidul Regency, Yogyakarta. Kukup Beach is still in line with Baron Beach, Krakal Beach, Sundak Beach, Sepanjang Beach and other beaches. Gunungkidul Regency is one of the areas in Yogyakarta with the largest collection of beaches. Countless number of beaches along the southern coast. There are still natural, there are also those who deliberately get a touch to make it more slick. One of them is Ngrawe Beach which is located in Kemadang, Gunungkidul. Ngobaran Beach is a natural tourist spot located in the cluster of seas on the south coast, precisely in Kanigoro Village, Saptosari sub-district, Gunungkidul Regency, Special Region of Yogyakarta, 2 km from Ngrenehan beach. coral covered with algae (green seaweed as a raw material for cosmetics) and there are many other marine biota that might get stuck in the coral pool. This is what supports the life of land fishermen, namely fishermen who do not need a boat or boat to get marine products, it is enough to move along the beach. The marine biotas that are often found are lobsters, sea urchins, shellfish, starfish and the seaweed itself, of course.
You can try Pulang Sawal Beach in Tepus District. Tourists are more familiar with the name Indrayanti to refer to this beach. Not only local visitors, foreign tourists are captivated by its charm.

Baron Beach is a tourist attraction in the form of a beach located in Kemadang Village, Tanjungsari District, Gunungkidul Regency. The location of Baron Beach can be reached 40 km from Yogyakarta city center. The origin of the name Baron Beach comes from the name of a nobleman from the Netherlands named Baron Skeber. The nobleman once landed his ship on the south coast, to be precise, on the beach which is currently known as Baron Beach. The road to the Baron Beach tourist attraction is good enough for private vehicles, motorbikes and buses to pass. The Baron Beach tourist object is a beach that forms a basin. Like other beaches, on Baron Beach there are various sea fish and their preparations. Fish that are usually sold at Baron Beach are tiger prawns, snapper, white pomfret and cob. Baron Beach has facilities in the form of a fish auction, children's playground, motorized boats, and a souvenir shop. Sirkaya fruit, horn plantain, soursop, and various kinds of souvenirs made from sea shells. Many souvenirs made from shells are sold at Baron Beach, namely brooches, shell curtains, decorative lamps, mirrors decorated with coral, figures, and various animal characters which are also made from sea shells. The sea alms ceremony is a ceremony that is still often performed by the people of Gunungkidul. Baron Beach is one of the places to hold the maritime alms ceremony. The sea alms ceremony is held every first Syuro date in the Javanese calendar. The maritime charity ceremony was performed as an expression of local gratitude for the abundance of fish catches in Baron Beach. Initially, most of the people around Baron Beach were not fishermen but farmers who cultivated the gardens. Once there was someone who started fishing on the beach and got a lot of fish, then many people followed him to catch fish. The longer the fish on the beach the less the population tried to catch the fish in the middle of the sea using wooden rafts. The existence of this ship on the beach because one day there was a fisherman tragedy that while fishing in the middle of the sea bitten by a shark, this news was spread everywhere and made the government donate boats for the fishermen on Baron Beach. The uniqueness of Baron Beach is the existence of an underground river which flowing swiftly towards the ocean. The underground river flows towards the sea and forms a river. The uniqueness of the underground river in Baron Beach is the taste of fresh water even though it is very close to the sea. Visitors who don't dare to play and swim in the sea can play in the water and swim in the underground river. Another view on Baron Beach is a hill around the beach. Visitors can enjoy the beauty of the beach from the top of the hill.

Pok Tunggal Beach or commonly called "the hidden paradise" is a tourist attraction in Yogyakarta, precisely in Tepus Village, Tepus, Gunung Kidul, Yogyakarta. If you count from the city, the distance is 80 km or about 2 hours drive. The name Pok Tunggal Beach is taken because on this beach there is an old duras tree that has stood firm to this day. This beach is surrounded by cliffs of karst hills. There are rock cliffs overgrown with dense trees and inhabited by tame monkeys. Uniquely, this beach has an underground freshwater river which is a source of life for the people around the coast. Like other southern beaches, Pok Tunggal Beach has fine white sand that stretches along the coast. Until now, Pok Tunggal Beach is still kept clean and natural. This beach is very crowded, both during holidays and weekdays. There are lots of activities offered at Pok Tunggal Beach, such as diving, snorkeling, swimming, camping, taking pictures in beautiful photo spots, to extreme activities such as rock climbing.

Almost all areas in the Dlingo area and its surroundings are overgrown with pine trees. One of them is the Asri Pine Forest area in Karangasem Hamlet. Because of its beauty, it's no wonder that many tourists come to take pictures. The cool air collaborates with the beautiful array of pine trees. If you pay attention, the view of these pine trees looks like the scenery in the Northwest Pacific. Moreover, the thin fog in the morning enveloped quietly.

Kebon Empring Market is a tourist attraction in Piyungan District which offers traditional culinary delights such as sego or wader rice, don't chili, sego catfish, sego welut, sego wiwit, tengkleng, sego mentel, geblek to dawet shell and chrysanthemums. The price offered is relatively cheap, starting from IDR 3,000 to IDR 17,000. Kebon Pring Market opened for tourist visits on May 17 2018. It is called Kebon Empring Market because almost all around the tourist attraction are bamboo trees or empring in Javanese. The location started to become a tourist attraction initially because many people took selfies on the Kali Gawe bridge in the Kebon Empring market location. After the Kali Gawe bridge was inaugurated in February 2018, four months later local residents took advantage of it and developed it into a tourist location by adding tourism supporting facilities and infrastructure such as parks, selfie destinations, bales above Kali Gawe.

Paragliding Hill Parangtritis is a tourist spot in Yogyakarta, this place presents views of Parangtritis beach from the top of the hill with an altitude of 900 meters above sea level and sunset views. Besides that, on Parangtritis Paragliding Hill there is an extreme sport of paragliding, for tourists who are interested, there are experts who accompany them. At first this hill was just an ordinary hill. Then in 1991 the first concrete runway was made which was used for paragliding. Then continued with the construction of pavilion facilities, stairs and parking areas in 1998

Dipowinatan Tourism Village is a village developed by the Yogyakarta Tourism Office for tourism purposes. The village is one of 17 currently being developed by the Yogyakarta City Government. In fact, Dipowinatan Village is located in Keparakan Village, Mergangsan District, Yogyakarta City. The main advantage highlighted by the village is the concept of live in or recreation that blends in with the surrounding community while blending in with the cultural elements and locality of the existing community. Inside the village, visitors will be offered several unique facilities such as visiting Javanese family homes wearing Javanese traditional clothing and adding artistic entertainment as well as Javanese culinary offerings.

The Watu Mabur Cliff area is relatively new to the public. This is indeed the case because previously the tourism potential in the Mangunan area had not been developed in such a way. Visiting the Watu Mabur Cliff is incomplete if you don't try some of the photo spots which are now very hits. The most famous photo spot is the highway / runway which ends right facing the ravine. So when you take a photo in this place it's like you're on an endless road.

Dahromo, Karang Asem, Muntuk, Dlingo, Bantul, Special Region of Yogyakarta 55783. Precisely on the hillside tourist route to the south of Lintang Sewu hill. Green Village Gedangsari Gunungkidul Tourism is quite an amazing natural tour, natural charm in the form of expanses of shady green trees and cool air, now there is even the longest flying fox ride in Southeast Asia. Located on a plateau, visitors can see panoramic views of the city of Jogja, Klaten to the city of Solo. Some fun holiday activities can be done while on vacation at Green Village Gunungkidul. Nglinggo Tea Garden Tourism is the only tea garden in Yogyakarta. Actually, this tea garden is a place of livelihood for the people around Pagerhajo. Then the residents had the idea to make it a tourist spot. With its natural charm, the Nglinggo Tea Garden is a well-known tourist attraction in Kulon Progo. The Nglinggo Tea Plantation is located in the Menoreh Hills area. The location is in Nglinggo Tourism Village, West Nglinggo, Pagerharjo, Samigaluh, Kulon Progo Regency, DIY. This tour offers a tourist attraction in the form of a stretch of tea plantations with an area of about 136 hectares at an altitude of 900-1000 meters above sea level. There visitors can see tea leaf pickers and can also harvest tea leaves. If you are not satisfied, visitors can also climb to the top of Mount Kukusan Kendeng, and will be spoiled with natural views that captivate the eye as well as the cool, unspoiled mountain air. From the peak, visitors will be presented with a view of eight large mountains in Jogja and Central Java. Visitors can also explore the Nglinggo Tea Plantation by jeep or trail bike. Even though it is open from 06.00-18.00 WIB, the Nglinggo Tea Garden can be used as a tourist attraction to hunt for the sunrise. Because visitors can spend the night in a home stay around. The entrance ticket price for the Nglinggo Tea Garden tourist attraction is IDR 5,000 per person.

For sunrise hunters who live or are domiciled in Yogyakarta and its surroundings, Geoforest Watu Payung Derivatives is the right destination. Not only for taking pictures, this tourist attraction is also suitable for just relaxing and enjoying the beauty of the morning.

Timang Beach is a tourist attraction in the form of a beach, namely the area that is the boundary between the sea and the land which is located in Gunungkidul Regency, Special Region of Yogyakarta. Puncak Segoro is the newest tourist destination in Yogyakarta that offers a dazzling sunset charm. Puncak Segoro Jogja itself is located on the edge of the southern coast of Yogyakarta. Borobudur (Javanese: ˆ??ˆ??ˆ??ˆ? ˆ??ƒ??ˆ??ˆ?®ˆ??ˆ??ˆ? ˆ??ˆ??, translit. Candi Barabudhur) is a Buddhist temple located in Borobudur, Magelang, Central Java, Indonesia. This temple is located approximately 100 km southwest of Semarang, 86 km west of Surakarta, and 40 km northwest of Yogyakarta. This stupa-shaped temple was founded by adherents of Mahayana Buddhism around the year 800 AD during the reign of the Syailendra dynasty. Borobudur is the largest Buddhist temple or shrine in the world, as well as one of the largest Buddhist monuments in the world. . Borobudur has the most complete and largest collection of Buddhist reliefs in the world. The largest main stupa is located in the center as well as crowning this building, surrounded by three circular rows of 72 perforated stupas in which there is a Buddha statue sitting cross-legged in a perfect lotus position with the Dharmachakra mudra (hand gesture) (turning the wheel of dharma). a model of the universe and built as a holy place to glorify Buddha as well as functioning as a place of pilgrimage to guide mankind from the world of worldly desires to enlightenment and wisdom according to Buddhist teachings. Pilgrims enter via the east side and start the ritual at the base of the temple by walking around this sacred building in a clockwise direction, while continuing to climb the next steps through three levels of realms in Buddhist cosmology. The three levels are KŽ madhŽtu (the realm of lust), Rupadhatu (the realm of form), and Arupadhatu (the realm of intangibility). On their way the pilgrims walked through a series of aisles and stairs witnessing no less than 1,460 beautiful relief panels engraved on the walls and balustrades. According to historical evidence, Borobudur was abandoned in the 14th century as the influence of the Hindu and Buddhist kingdoms on Java weakened. and began to enter the influence of Islam. The world began to realize the existence of this building since it was discovered in 1814 by Sir Thomas Stamford Raffles, who at that time served as Governor General of England over Java. Since then Borobudur has undergone a series of rescue and restoration efforts. The largest restoration project was carried out in the period 1975 to 1982 on the efforts of the Government of the Republic of Indonesia and UNESCO, then this historic site was included in the list of World Heritage Sites. Borobudur is now still used as a place of religious pilgrimage; every year Buddhists who come from all over Indonesia and abroad gather at Borobudur to commemorate the Vesak Trisuci. In the world of tourism, Borobudur is the single tourist attraction in Indonesia which is the most visited by tourists.

Indrayanti Beach offers stunning natural beauty. The stretch of sand and the blue sea is a charm that is second to none. Indrayanti Beach is one of Yogyakarta's tourist attractions which is a recommendation for tourists. If you feel bored in Malioboro, this beach can be the choice.

Nglambor Beach is an exotic beach located in Purwodadi Village, Tepus District, Gunung Kidul, Special Region of Yogyakarta. The location is just west of Siung Beach and east of Jogan Beach. The distance is approximately 74 km from downtown Jogja, this beach offers beautiful panoramic views of the coast. There are two large rocks that resemble turtles right in front of the bay. The clear sea water allows visitors to freely see coral, seaweed, fish with various colors chasing each other, and various other marine biota from the surface of the water. Visitors can also snorkel and swim at this beach without having to worry about being rolled over by big waves because the location of the beach is in the bay. Often visitors come from out of town and even abroad, such as tourists from the Netherlands, France and Singapore.

Ullen Sentalu Museum, (Javanese: ˆ??ˆ??ˆ?ñˆ??ˆ?¦ˆ??ˆ??ˆ??ƒ??ˆ??ˆ?ˆ??ˆ?ˆ?§ˆ??ˆ? ?ƒ??ˆ?ñˆ?¬ˆ??ˆ??ˆ? ˆ?ˆ??, translit. Ull??n Sentalu Museum) located in Pakem District (Kaliurang), Sleman Regency, Yogyakarta Special Region, is a museum that displays the culture and life of the nobles of the Mataram dynasty (Surakarta, Sultanate of Yogyakarta, Praja Mangkunegaran, and Pakualaman Duchy) along with a collection of various batik (both Yogyakarta and Surakarta styles). worn, both for formal events and for everyday. \nThe name Ullen Sentalu is an acronym from the Javanese language: "ULating blencong SEjatiNe TAtaraning Lumaku" which means "Blencong lamp as a guide for mankind in walking and pursuing life". This philosophy is taken from an oil lamp used in wayang kulit performances (blencong) which is a light that is always moving to direct and illuminate our journey in life. This museum was founded by a Yogyakarta aristocrat who is known to be very close to the Surakarta and Yogyakarta royal families. There are also various histories regarding the state of Javanese culture from the Ancient Mataram period to the Islamic Mataram with all its rules. The state of a well-built museum is able to make visitors feel as if they are absorbed into the amazing ancient Javanese period.

Pindul Cave is a tourist attraction in the form of a cave located in Bejiharjo Village, Karangmojo District, Gunungkidul Regency. Pindul Cave is known for its way of exploring the cave which is done by riding a float tube over an underground river in the cave, this activity is known as cave tubing.

Who would have thought that Yogyakarta even has its own "Kuta" namely Sepanjang Beach, one of the beaches in Gunungkidul Regency. This area does have countless collections of beautiful beaches. Even this beach is predicted as 'Kuta Tempo Doeloe'. Indeed, what kind of charm does this beach offer?

Krakal Beach is a strategic beach for a stopover, besides being able to enjoy panoramic views of the sea, tourists can also taste seafood. There is an icon in the form of a fish-shaped building on a hill which is often used as a photo spot.

Glagah Indah Beach is one of the beaches which is a tourist attraction in the province of the Special Region of Yogyakarta. Glagah Indah Beach is one of the beaches in Yogyakarta with black sand that contains a lot of iron sand. Glagah Indah Beach has good access

Siung Beach is a beach tourism object located in Kec. Tepus, to be exact, is in Duwet Hamlet, Purwodadi Village, Tepus District, Gunungkidul Regency, Special Region of Yogyakarta province. The location is approximately 75 km from the city of Yogya and has a rock climbing route with 250 international standard routes. Along the way to the beach location, you will be treated to views of limestone hills overgrown with teak trees. The winding and ascending road is a challenge that you must pass before reaching Siung Beach. However, the tiring journey will pay off when you are already in the Siung Beach area. The beach with white sand and the sound of the waves, will make your mood and mind calm and peaceful. Because this beach is very remote, the facilities available are minimal. For lodging accommodations are not yet available here, but if you want to spend the night at Siung Beach, you can use a climber's hut which looks like a house on stilts with a capacity of around 20 people. If you want to spend the night in a natural atmosphere, you can bring your own tent which you can use in the camping ground area. If you are from Yogyakarta City, you can use the Yogyakarta-Wonosari-Tepus-Purwodadi-Siung Beach route. If you use public transportation, you can use the bus from Yogyakarta Giwangan Terminal by taking the Jogja-Wonosari bus. Arriving at the Wonosari terminal, you can use public transportation for the Wonosari-Jepitu route. Arriving at the Purwodadi Village Hall T-junction, you can use a motorcycle taxi service, because that's the only public transportation that can be used to get to Siung Beach.

Jogja's Sadranan Beach is a hidden gem diamond that suddenly appears, from within a pile of treasures of a row of beautiful beaches in Jogja. Like other beaches in the southern region of Jogja, Sadranan Beach also has the characteristics of white sand with coral reefs in an area very close to the shoreline. This white sand is reminiscent of famous beaches such as Kuta in Bali and Mandalika in Lombok. However, this beach in Gunung Kidul has the advantages of the 2 famous beaches, namely the presence of coral reefs on the beach. In addition, this beach is also relatively quiet. These two advantages allow visitors to really enjoy the beauty of the beach without having to be disturbed by the hustle and bustle of humans.

On Nguluran beach you can only see the vast expanse of sea and photo spots. All of these facilities are on the cliff. About a dozen meters from the water surface of the beach. The sensation that arises is like walking on a rope at a height of dozens of meters above sea water. But there's no need to worry, the manager guarantees the safety of the visitors, as long as they don't violate the rules that have been made by the manager.

Samas Beach (Javanese: ˆ?ˆ?ñˆ??ˆ?ñˆ??ˆ??ƒ??ˆ?ñˆ??ˆ?ñˆ??, translit. Pasisir Samas) is one of the beaches that located on a row of beaches east of Parangtritis Beach. The location of Samas Beach is approximately 14 km south of Bantul City or about 35 km from the center of Yogyakarta City, precisely in Srigading Village, Sanden District, Bantul Regency, Yogyakarta Special Region.

Drini Beach is a tourist attraction located in Banjarejo Village, Tanjungsari District, Gunungkidul, Yogyakarta. It is located east of Baron Beach and is about 1 km to the east of Sepanjang Beach. However, the actual distance that must be taken to get to this beach is 60 km or about 2-3 hours from the city of Yogyakarta. The infrastructure leading to Drini Beach is quite smooth, although the entrance to this beach is quite steep and winding. Drini Beach is a beach directly facing the Indian Ocean. This beach has a fairly steep coastal slope of about 10 degrees and is part of Wonosari which is dominated by karst rocks from Mount Sewu. This beach has not been touched by many local and foreign tourists, because of its location in a remote area. Thus, Drini Beach is known as the Virgin Beach. This term is used by the local community because the condition of Drini Beach is still clean, the air is cool, the water feels cold coupled with a dazzling stretch of white sand and the water flow is not as violent as Parangtritis Beach. This beach has a large cliff in the middle of the beach. and divides this beach into two sides, namely the west side and the east side. This cliff looks so beautiful that it looks like a small island floating in the middle of the beach. On this rock a lighthouse was built where from the tower our eyes will be spoiled with an extraordinarily beautiful view. On this beach visitors can also see clearly the seaweed between the sea corals and other marine biota.

Sri Gethuk Waterfall is a natural tourist attraction located in Playen District, Gunungkidul Regency, Yogyakarta. This waterfall is on the banks of the Oyo River, so to enjoy it, you have to go along the river with a raft. Along the way, you will be treated to views of limestone cliffs on either side and lush trees. If in the dry season, the river water will be very clear, greenish in color and calm. Sri Gethuk Waterfall has 3 springs, namely Ngandong, Dong Poh, and Ngumbul springs. These three springs gather and flow through a high cliff to form the Sri Gethuk waterfall. Sri Gethuk Waterfall has a height of about 25 meters with 3-5 waterfalls depending on the season. The water that never dries up does not fall into a pool but immediately crawls over the neat limestone rocks on the riverbank. This waterfall is currently in the development stage to become a mainstay tourist destination for Gunungkidul Regency apart from beaches and karst mountains. Sri Gethuk Waterfall is also known as Slempret Waterfall. The name Slempret itself comes from a legend in Bleberan Village. According to stories circulating in the community, this waterfall is the center of the jinn led by Jin Anggo Menduro. This waterfall originates from three springs, namely Kedungpoh, Ngandong, and Ngumbul. The three springs flow into one and form water droplets that fall from the barren karst rock cliffs.

Sewu Temple or Manjusrighra (Hanacaraka:ˆ??ˆ??ˆ??ˆ? ˆ??ƒ??ˆ?ñˆ?§ˆ??ˆ??, Javanese: Candi S??wu) is a Buddhist temple built in the 11th century. 8 AD which is only eight hundred meters to the north of Prambanan Temple. Sewu Temple is the second largest Buddhist temple complex after Borobudur Temple in Central Java. Sewu Temple is older than Borobudur and Prambanan Temples. Even though it originally had 249 temples, the local people called this temple "Sewu" which means a thousand in Javanese. This naming is based on the legend of Loro Jonggrang. Administratively, the Sewu Temple complex is located in Bener Hamlet, Bugisan Village, Prambanan District, Klaten Regency, Central Java Province.

Wediombo Beach (Javanese O: Wedhiamba) is a beach located in Jepitu Village, Girisubo, Gunungkidul near Siung Beach, 80 km from the city of Yogyakarta. The beach includes a bay surrounded by rocky mountains and white sand. In the middle of the sea, the rocks stand out. This place is also used for surfing. The height of the waves can reach 3-4 meters. Wediombo Beach faces west and the sun is on the south side (November-May). From this beach, people can see the sunset in the evening. Apart from surfing, Wediombo also has natural pools to waters without waves. There is also a place for snorkeling. Wediombo is one of 13 places that are included in the Gunung Sewu UNESCO World Nature Reserve.

Jogan Beach is a beach tourism object located in Duwet Hamlet, Purwodadi, Tepus, Gunungkidul Regency, Special Region of Yogyakarta. The location is approximately 74 km from Yogyakarta city center. This beach is located in the Gunungkidul mountain range, which provides a natural view of cliffs and waterfalls that lead to the open sea.

Ngrenehan Beach is a fishing beach. Located in the village of Kanigoro, Saptosari District, approximately 30 km south of the city of Wonosari. A beach in the form of a bay surrounded by a stretch of limestone hills and has a very stunning panorama with the waves hitting the white sand. Tourists can watch fishermen's activities and enjoy ready-to-eat fish or bring fresh fish as souvenirs.

Jungwok Beach is a beach located in Jepitu Village, Girisubo District, Gunungkidul Regency, Special Region of Yogyakarta. Jungwok Beach is one of the beaches that has a beautiful panorama with white sand that is typical of beaches in Gunung Kidul. Jungwok Beach is located to the east of Wediombo Beach and to the west of Ngusalan Beach. Jungwok Beach is about 40 km from Wonosari City. Road access to Jungwook Beach is still quite difficult, that's because the road is still not paved. Jungwok Beach is often a tourist destination because it is a convenient place for camping.

In Gunungkidul Regency, it is not difficult to choose a beach that is still quiet and beautiful. Greweng Beach in Girisubo District is one of them. Not only beautiful, this beach is also known as a destination for camping. However, prepare more energy to reach its remote location.

Sedahan Beach has a coastline that is quite long and wide enough to be used as a playground. On both sides of the beach, there are cliffs that flank this beach and jut out into the sea. Sedahan Beach has waves that are typical of the South Sea and stretches of white sand with fine grains. The clear, fresh, and sparkling turquoise water in the sunlight will hypnotize anyone to play in the water and throw themselves on the beach. However, visitors must be careful because the south coast always has strong currents and waves, so visitors are not advised to swim too far from the mainland. Sedahan Beach is also known by many people as a fun fishing location. Many visitors are willing and take the time to come far and wide just to fish at Sedahan Beach.

Watu Kodok Beach is one of the beaches in Gunung Kidul. Watu Kodok Beach has white sand and beautiful blue sea water. On this beach there are several steep rocks, these rocks are an attraction for tourists and are unique to the beach itself. And the atmosphere of an unspoiled beach also makes this beach its main attraction, but this beach is still classified as a new beach so there are still not many tourists. Watu Kodok Beach is perfect for those of you who want to spend vacation time with your family.

In general, the beach is synonymous with sand, isn't it, but Kesirat beach has its own uniqueness which you will find here. Kesirat beach has no sand, but you will find cliffs that have beautiful structures, then you can enjoy the beach above, this place is also very suitable for enjoying the sunset. The beauty of this beach makes everyone unable to forget it like a former promise hehee.. Kesirat beach has instagramable photo spots which are perfect for those of you who like to take pictures. Another uniqueness that characterizes Kesirat Beach tourism is the presence of a tree that seems to stand firm which has become the icon of this tourist spot. Many tourists use this tree as a background for their photos.

Ngandong Beach is located in Sidoarjo Village, Tepus District, Gunung Kidul Regency, Yogyakarta. This beach is actually not far from the more famous Indrayanti Beach, precisely located in the northwest of Indrayanti beach. Ngandong Beach is a small beach but has its own characteristics which are an attraction for tourists. Even so, not many tourists know this beach tourist destination. This beach is crowded with visitors during the holiday season, but quiet on weekdays.

Galaxy Waterpark is a water recreation park that stands on an area of 2.5 hectares, which is sufficient to accommodate visitors during holidays. With a very wide location, there are many rides and facilities that you can enjoy. In this place there are also several pools, from a children's pool to an adult pool. In addition, the facilities provided by the manager are also quite complete to support your comfort while on vacation.

The Pulesari Tourism Village is increasingly adding to the profile of tourist villages in Jogja which was born from people's awareness of their local potential. Both in terms of cultural diversity, natural charm around, culinary treasures, as well as historical and cultural values that exist. Everything is packed in a tourist excitement. The location of Pulesari Tourism Village is in Sleman Regency, Special Region of Yogyakarta (DIY), which incidentally is a district that is blessed with various tourist attractions. The presence of the Pulesari Tourism Village seems to be a patch for an incomplete tourist puzzle. And this is a review of Pulosari Tourism Village as an initial reference for determining future vacation locations.

Tembi Tourism Village, is one of many tourist villages that has successfully managed its area, so that it becomes an area worth visiting. The natural, historical and cultural potential of the Tembi Tourism Village is indeed very suitable to be made a tourist village. Moreover, the distance of Tembi Tourism Village is not far from downtown Jogja. Apparently, the charm of the beauty of Tembi Tourism Village is not only limited to these two things. And here is complete information about Tembi Tourism Village, as an initial reference for determining tourist locations during the holidays. The location of Tembi Tourism Village is one way to Parangtritis. The address for Tembi Tourism Village is Tembi Village, Sewon District, Bantul Regency, Special Region of Yogyakarta.

Jogja is always interesting to kidnap, especially its tourist spots. Various tours are available in Jogja, ranging from man-made tours to natural tours. Like the Kaliurang Tourism Park, which combines natural elements with recreational parks. This recreational park is located on the slopes of Mount Merapi. It's not strange if this tourist attraction is very cool. Spending time on vacation here is the right choice.

HeHa Sky View is one of the newest tourist attractions in Yogyakarta and is currently the most popular. Do you want an aesthetic photo in the style of a celebrity or take a photo on a rooftop with a glass floor? Can! .Located in romantic Yogyakarta, Heha Sky View is a tourist spot that has three distinct characteristics. Based on their Instagram account, the three main features of Heha Sky View are selfies, restaurants and food stalls. There are many contemporary food vendors with container concepts for those of you who like to pamper your tongue. And if you want to add to your selfie stock, there are lots of Instagrammable spots that are worth trying.

Mudal River Park, an open natural tourist attraction located in Kulon Progo Regency, which offers the charm of a bathing pool sourced from natural springs. The spring comes from a cave, so that the existence of the Mudal River Park eliminates the haunted impression of a cave. Moreover, coupled with the support of facilities that make the tourists feel comfortable while there. Mudal River Park is one of the Kulon Progo tours which is always the main destination when the holidays arrive. One of the main reasons is because the Mudal River Park can be a fun family tourist destination.

Sangen Beach. The location is in Kemadang Village, Gunung Kidul. This beautiful beach does sound foreign to the ear, but it turns out that this beach has a very calming beauty. The condition of the waves quietly drifting away makes us have to be careful if we want to play in the water when it's high tide, but when it's low tide you can play the waves around the beach. Not far from the beach area there is a hill with tree decorations that are still shady and green in nature. You can climb up the hill via the stairs that have been provided.

Apart from Glagah Beach and Trisik Beach, it turns out that there is one more beach in Kulon Progo. Namely Congot Beach, this one beach is famous as a fishing paradise. So it's no wonder that Congot Beach is visited by many fishing maniacs. Apart from that, the people around Congot Beach depend on their livelihood as fishermen. Congot Beach is indeed not as popular as other beaches in Kulon Progo. It began to be visited by many tourists when the Pasir Mendit Mangrove Forest opened. Because the location is not too far from Congot Beach, which is on the west coast. Congot Beach is the estuary of the Bogowonto River. This is also what causes Congot Beach to become a favorite spot for anglers, because there are many types of fish available, ranging from fresh water fish, brackish water fish to salt water fish.

Mount Tangkuban Parahu is a mountain located in West Java Province, Indonesia. About 20 km to the north of Bandung City, with lush pine trees and a stretch of tea gardens around it, Mount Tangkuban Parahu has a height of 2,084 meters. The shape of this mountain is Stratovulcano with an eruption center that moves from east to west. The type of rock that is released through eruptions is mostly lava and sulfur, the mineral that is released is sulfuric sulfur, the mineral that is released when the volcano is inactive is sulfur vapor. The Mount Tangkuban Parahu area is managed by Perum Perhutanan. The average daily temperature is 17oC during the day and 2 ?øC at night.

Jalan Braga is the name of a main street in the city of Bandung, Indonesia. The name of this street is well known since the reign of the Dutch East Indies. Until now the name of the street is still maintained as one of the mascots and tourist attractions of the city of Bandung, which was formerly known as Parijs van Java.

Gedung Sate, with its trademark form of a skewer ornament on its central tower, has long been a landmark or landmark for the city of Bandung which is not only known to the people in West Java, but also throughout Indonesia. in West java. For example, the shape of the building in front of the Tasikmalaya Railway Station. Starting construction in 1920, this white building still stands strong but elegant and now functions as the central government building for West Java. eldest Mayor of Bandung, Bertus Coops and Petronella Roelofsen, representing the Governor General in Batavia, JP Graaf van Limburg Stirum on July 27, 1920, was the result of the planning of a team consisting of Ir.J.Gerber, a well-known young architect who graduated from the Delft Nederland Faculty of Engineering , Ir. Er. De Roo and Ir. G. Hendriks and the Gemeente van Bandoeng, chaired by Col. pur. VL. Slors involved 2,000 workers, 150 of whom were carvers, or bongpay experts, carvers of tombstones and woodcarvers of Chinese nationality who came from Confucian or Cantonese origin, assisted by stone masons, stir workers and servers from residents of Sekeloa Village, Coblong Dago Village, Kampung Gandok and Cibarengkok Village, which previously they worked on Gedong Sirap (ITB Campus) and Gedong Papak (Bandung City Hall). Post, Telephone and Telegraph) and Libraries. The architecture of Gedung Sate is the work of architect Ir.
