J.Gerber and his group cannot be separated from the input of the Dutch architect maestro Dr. Hendrik Petrus Berlage, who has the nuances of the face of traditional Indonesian architecture. Indo-European architecture, (Indo Europeeschen architectuur stijl), so it is not impossible that the elegance of the Borobudur Temple will also color Gedung Sate. Some opinions about the splendor of Gedung Sate include Cor Pashier and Jan Wittenberg, two Dutch architects, who said "the architectural style of Gedung Sate is the experimental style of the architect which leads to the form of Indo-European architectural styles".
D. Ruhl in his book Bandoeng en haar Hoogvlakte 1952, "Gedung Sate is the most beautiful building in Indonesia". HP Berlage, during a visit to Gedung Sate April 1923, stated, "Gedung Sate is a major architectural work, which successfully combines eastern and western styles in harmony". As with the Italian architectural style during the renaissance, especially in the west wing building. Meanwhile, the terraced tower in the middle of the building looks like a meru or pagoda roof. There are many more opinions of Indonesian architects who state the splendor of Gedung Sate, for example Slamet Wirasonjaya, and Ir. Harnyoto Kunto. 
The strength and integrity of Gedung Sate to this day cannot be separated from the materials and construction techniques used. The walls of Gedung Sate are made of large stone chips (1 ? 1 ? 2 m) taken from the rocky hills in eastern Bandung around Arcamanik and Mount Manglayang. The construction of the Gedung Sate building uses a professional conventional method with due observance of technical standards. I 212,976 m?ý, Second floor 3,023,796 m?ý, second floor terrace 212,976 m?ý, tower 121 m?ý and tower terrace 205,169 m?ý. 
Gerber himself combines several architectural styles into his design. For the windows, Gerber takes the Spanish Moorish theme, while the building is Italian Renaissance. Especially for the tower, Gerber incorporates Asian flow, namely the roof style of Balinese temples or pagodas in Thailand. At the top there is a "skewer" with 6 skewer ornaments (another version says water guava or jasmine), which represents 6 million guilders - the amount used to build Gedung Sate. Ornaments made of stone, located above the main door of Gedung Sate, are often associated with the Borobudur temple because of their similar shape. The facade (front view) of Gedung Sate turns out to be very calculated. By following the north-south axis (which is also applied to Pakuan Building, which faces Mount Malabar in the south), Gedung Sate was deliberately built to face Mount Tangkuban Perahu in the north. the center of government of the Dutch East Indies after Batavia was deemed no longer eligible as a center of government because of its development, so it was used by the Bureau of Public Works. On December 3, 1945, an incident occurred that killed seven youths who defended Gedung Sate from attacks by Gurkha troops. To commemorate the seven youths, a stone monument was made which was placed behind the Gedung Sate courtyard. By order of the Minister of Public Works on December 3, 1970 the monument was moved to the forecourt of Gedung Sate. Since 1980, Gedung Sate has been known as the Governor's Office because it was the center of activities for the West Java Provincial Government, which previously occupied the Kerta Mukti Building in Jalan Braga Bandung. The Governor's office is on the second floor along with the offices of the Deputy Governor, Regional Secretary, Assistants and Bureau. At present the Governor is assisted by three Deputy Governors who handle the Governance Sector, the Economic and Development Sector, as well as the People's Welfare Sector, a Regional Secretary and four Assistants namely Administrative Assistant, Development Administration Assistant, Social Welfare Assistant and Administrative Assistant. occupy Gedung Sate. The Social Welfare Assistant and Administrative Assistant together with staff occupy the New Building.
To the east and west there are two large rooms that will remind you of a ballroom which is often found in European community buildings. This room is more commonly known as the west hall and east hall, often used for official activities. Around these two halls there are rooms occupied by several Bureaus with their staff. At the top there is a floor called Menara Gedung Sate, this floor cannot be seen from below, to go to the top floor using the elevator or by climbing a wooden ladder. The magnificent perfection of Gedung Sate is complemented by the New Building which takes a bit of the architectural style of Gedung Sate but with a contextual style created by architect Ir. Sudibyo which was built in 1977 for the Leaders and Members of the Regional Representatives Council of West Java Province in carrying out their duties and functions as a Legislative Body Region.
Gedung Sate has become one of the tourist destinations in the city of Bandung. Particularly for foreign tourists, many of them deliberately visit because they have emotional and historical ties to this building. This connection between emotion and history might be felt more fully if you climb the available steps one by one to the Gedung Sate tower. There are 6 stairs that must be traversed with 10 steps each that must be climbed. The beauty of this park is often used as a location for activities that have a family feel, a location for shooting music video clips for both local and national artists, a location for family photos or self-portraits and even photos of the wedding couple. relax, just sit around enjoying the fresh air of the city of Bandung or do some light exercise. Comparing Gedung Sate with the central government buildings (capitol buildings) in many national capitals doesn't seem like an exaggeration. The similarities are all built in the middle of a green complex with a magnificent central tower. Especially in terms of the location of the Sate building and its landscape which is relatively similar to the White House in Washington, DC, United States. It can be said that Gedung Sate is the "White House" of Bandung.

Trans Studio Bandung is an integrated tourism area in the city of Bandung, Indonesia. Trans Studio was built on an area of 4.2 hectares with an investment of Rp 2 trillion, making it the largest and most comprehensive entertainment area in Bandung. The existing rides offer new adventures and sensations that are no less challenging than their predecessor, namely Trans Studio Resort Makassar which opened in 2009. Trans Studio Bandung opened to the public on June 18, 2011. Trans Studio Bandung is the most complete playground in the city of Bandung

Forest Park Ir. H. Djuanda (Tahura Djuanda) is a conservation area that is integrated between secondary nature and plantation forests of the Pinus type (Pinus merkusil) located in the Cikapundung River Sub-Watershed and the Citarum Watershed which stretches from Curug Dago, Dago Pakar to Curug Maribaya which is part of the Gunung Pulosari forest group. Tahura Djuanda is located to the north of Bandung City, approximately 7 km from the city center, geographically located at 1070 30' East Longitude and 60 52' South Latitude, administratively it is in the Ciburial Village area, Cimenyan District, Bandung Regency and partly in Mekarwangi Village, Cibodas Village, Langensari Village, and Wangunharja Village, Lembang District, West Bandung Regency and Dago Village, Coblong District, Bandung City. 526.98 ha.

As one of the new Lembang tourist attractions, the Lembang Farmhouse began operating around 2015. Tourist attractions in Bandung are usually helped by social media, especially Facebook and Instagram. This place seems to maximize this. With a European-style design, there are many unique spots that will definitely be interesting for selfies and posting on social media. indeed, Farmhouse Lembang so far offers 'photo tours' as its main attraction. Similar to Dago Dream Park, only the concept of the place is different.

Bandung Zoo is one of the natural attractions of flora and fauna in the city of Bandung, West Java, Indonesia. The Bandung Zoo is located adjacent to the Bandung Institute of Technology campus and the Cikapundung River.

Kawah Putih is a tourist spot in West Java which is located in Alam Endah Village, Rancabali District, Bandung Regency, West Java, which is located at the foot of Mount Patuha. White crater is a lake formed from the eruption of Mount Patuha. The soil mixed with sulfur around this crater is white, then the color of the water in this crater is greenish white. What is unique about this crater is that the water sometimes changes color. Kawah Putih Lake itself is at an altitude of 2194 m but the total area of Kawah Putih Lake is 25 ha which is used for tourism 5 ha and the location of the crater itself is 3 ha.

Tebing Keraton or Tebing Karaton is a cliff located in the Forest Park area of Ir. H. Djuanda. This cliff is located in Kampung Ciharegem Puncak, Ciburial Village, Bandung, West Java, Indonesia. From the Keraton Cliffs you can enjoy spectacular views. Not city lights, but forest!

Dusun Bambu is a recreational park based on ecotourism in West Java with the concept of 'Private Sanctuary Lifestyle' (Healthy Tourism Concept). Through this concept, Dusun Bambu is ready to provide recreational facilities that are safe and comfortable by always implementing strict health protocol standards. Combining the beauty of nature and traditional culture, the facilities at Dusun Bambu are designed for the most memorable natural tourism experiences, starting from leisurely walks, cycling, enjoying delicious culinary delights amidst natural charm, to visiting replicas of traditional villages. There is also the capacity for daily visits to Dusun Bambu to ensure that social distancing recommendations are carried out. That way, Dusun Bambu is ready to guarantee the safety of your tourist visit, presenting an irreplaceable visiting experience and a satisfying exploration of tastes.

The Geological Museum was founded on May 16, 1929. The museum has been renovated with funding from JICA (Japan International Cooperation Agency). After undergoing renovations, the Geological Museum was reopened and inaugurated by the Vice President of the Republic of Indonesia, Megawati Soekarnoputri on August 23, 2000. As a historical monument, the museum is under government protection and is a national heritage. In this museum, abundant geological materials are stored and managed, such as fossils, rocks, minerals. These were collected during fieldwork in Indonesia since 1850.

The Museum of the Asian-African Conference is one of the museums in the city of Bandung, which is located at Jalan Asia Afrika No. 65. This museum is the memorabilia of the Asian-African Conference. This museum has a very close relationship with Gedung Merdeka. Overall Merdeka Building has two main buildings, the first is called Merdeka Building as the main meeting place, while next to Merdeka Building is the Museum of the Asian-African Conference as a place for memorabilia of the Asian-African Conference. The background for the construction of this museum is the desire of the leaders of the nations in Asia and Africa to know about the Merdeka Building and its surroundings where the Asian-African Conference was taking place. This made the Minister of Foreign Affairs of the Republic of Indonesia, Prof. Dr. Mochtar Kusumaatmadja, SH, LL.M had an idea to build a museum. He conveyed the idea at the Committee meeting for the 25th anniversary of the Asian-African Conference (1980) which was attended by the Director General of Culture Prof. Dr. Haryati Soebadio as a representative from the Ministry of Education and Culture. Then the museum was inaugurated on April 24, 1980 to coincide with the 25th anniversary of the Asian-African Conference.

The Great Mosque of Bandung, West Java Province, formerly known as the Great Mosque of Bandung, is a mosque located in the city of Bandung, West Java, Indonesia. The status of this mosque is as a provincial mosque for West Java. This mosque was first built in 1810, and since its founding, the Great Mosque has undergone eight renovations in the 19th century, then five times in the 20th century until it was finally renovated again in 2001 until the inauguration of the Great Mosque of Bandung on June 4, 2003 which was inaugurated by the Governor of West Java at that time, HR Nuriana. This new mosque, which has an Arabic style, replaces the old Great Mosque, which has a distinctive Sundanese style. The Great Mosque of Bandung, as we can see now, has two twin towers on the left and right sides of the 81 meter high mosque which are always open to the public every day. Saturday and Sunday. The roof of the mosque was changed from the joglo roof to a large dome on the middle roof and smaller ones on the left and right sides of the roof of the mosque and the walls of the mosque were made of high quality natural stone. Now the total land area of the mosque is 23,448 mý with a building area of 8,575 mý and can accommodate around 13,000 worshippers.
Dago Dreampark is a contemporary tour in the city of Bandung with an area of 13 hectares that carries the Javanese - Sundanese & Balinese concept equipped with various interesting facilities & rides.

Orchid Forest Cikole Lembang has been established since August 2017. This place is the largest orchid garden in Indonesia. Located in the middle of a protected forest area and spans 12 hectares. There are at least 157 types of various kinds of orchids developed here. Orchid Forest Cikole Bandung focuses on introducing and cultivating various orchid plants. Using local and international methods. The orchid species don't only come from Indonesia, which is the second country with the most variants of orchids. Orchid plants in the Orchid Forest also come from other countries, such as Venezuela, Argentina, the Philippines, Peru and the United States.

Punclut which stands for Ciumbuleuit Peak is one of the areas located in the north of Bandung City. This area is located 7 kilometers from downtown Bandung. On weekends, the Punclut area is filled with tourists who come to tour and enjoy the view of the city of Bandung. Many residents and tourists use this area to do morning walks or exercise every Sunday.
Bandung Alun-alun is the center of the city of Bandung which is characterized by a large plot of land. All around there are functional buildings. The place is near the Grote Postweg.

The Sri Baduga Museum is a museum located in the city of Bandung, West Java, Indonesia. This museum is managed by the West Java provincial government, which was founded in 1974 by utilizing the old building of the former Kawedanan Tegallega, which was then inaugurated on June 5, 1980 by The Minister of Education and Culture at that time, Daoed Joesoef. And then it was determined through Kepmendikbud number 02223/0/1990 dated 4 April 1990.

Rabbit Town Bandung is one of the unique tours in Bandung which was founded on January 11 2018. A tourist spot that makes rabbits the main icon. All of the decorations are made to look as cute as possible and also display various types of cute rabbits. Visitors who are interested in this animal can bring a rabbit home by buying it first. This tourist spot is owned by the Chairman of the Kaum Group, Mr. Henry Husada. Mr. Henry himself deliberately made one of his houses, which has an area of two hectares with 30 rooms, a unique tourist attraction. Apart from the presence of rabbit species, this place also offers good photo spots. Not only that, in this tour there are also several rides for children so that visitors who bring their children will feel at home for long.

Stone Garden, is the name for a stretch of land filled with beautiful irregular rock formations and forms a natural garden. Bandung has many extraordinary natural attractions. It turns out that Bandung has natural cave tourism, namely Pawon Cave and Stone Garden tours. Pawon Cave is a cave that was formed in ancient times. This cave was used by early humans as a shelter. And uniquely above Pawon Cave there is a very beautiful expanse of rocks with extraordinary views known as the Stone Garden. No less beautiful than the natural attractions of Tangkuban Perahu, Ciwidey White Crater and Situ Patengan are natural tourist areas that are often visited by many local and foreign tourists.

The city of Bandung never seems to run out of creative ideas in developing tourist destinations. Various vacation destinations are available here, ranging from culinary, historical, to educational tours. The packaging is also unique and attractive, like the one in The Great Asia Africa. This newest tourist area in Lembang offers the experience of exploring several countries on two continents, in line with its name.

Bandung as a tourist destination is never ending. Supported by beautiful landscapes, the Bandung area is able to attract the attention of tourists. Both in terms of nature, culture, culinary, and creative arts simultaneously. Of the many tourist attractions available, Bukit Moko Bandung has become one of the most popular names in recent years. Located at an altitude of about 1500 meters above sea level, Moko Hill has cool weather. For visitors who are not used to this weather, it is better to bring a thick jacket, especially if you come during the rainy season.

Mount Papandayan is a strato volcano located in Garut Regency, West Java, precisely in Cisurupan District. The mountain with an altitude of 2665 meters above sea level is located about 70 km southeast of the city of Bandung. On Mount Papandayan, there are several famous craters. Among them are the Mas Crater, the Baru Crater, the Nangklak Crater and the Manuk Crater. The craters emit steam from the inside. The topography in the area is steep, hilly and mountainous and there are steep cliffs. According to Schmidt and Ferguson's classification, it includes climate type B, with an average rainfall of 3,000 mm/year, humidity of 70 ? 80% and temperature of 10 ?øC.

Amazing Art World Bandung, a tourist attraction located in Bandung, which emphasizes that tourist destinations are not just about beaches, waterfalls or other natural attractions. The results of the painting turned out to be able to become a very pleasant tourist destination. Moreover, 3D painting, apart from being cool, is able to manipulate the visitors' eyes. The extent of Amazing Art World Bandung makes it one of the largest 3D painting museums, not only at the national level, but in the world.

Dutch Cave Bandung is a cave located in an area that is now designated as Ir. H. Djuanda is a stretch of mountains from West to East which is a "giant natural water tank" for reserves in the dry season. In the Cikapundung River Basin area in the Forest Park Ir. H. Djuanda during the Dutch occupation built the Bengkok Hydroelectric Power Plant (PLTA), which was the first hydroelectric power plant in Indonesia in 1918, where the tunnel passed through tuffaceous sandstone hills.

Bandung City Hall Park is a city park located in the city of Bandung. This park is located south of Bandung City Hall. Currently, the Bandung City Hall Park consists of two integrated parks, namely Dewi Sartika Park and Rhino Park. The two parks were inaugurated by the Mayor of Bandung at the time, Ridwan Kamil, on December 19 2017.

Panghegar Waterboom Bandung is one of the tourist destinations that must be visited for tourists who want to invite their children to play in the water. Located in Buah Batu, this location is often targeted on weekends. Not only serving a swimming pool, this place also provides a variety of interesting rides that are a shame if you miss them. It consists of water slides divided into 2 categories, namely adult slides and children's slides. Family recreation destinations offer a variety of fun activities, both for children and adults. There are several types of pools that you can try: wave pool, mini pool, lazy river, and so on. There is also the newest one at Panghegar Waterboom Bandung, which is a hot spring pool that is served for tourists who want to soak.

Mount Manglayang is a stratovolcano type mountain which is located between Bandung City and Sumedang Regency, West Java, Indonesia and has an altitude of around 1818 meters above sea level. The scenery is quite beautiful, but because it is relatively not too high, so it is not well known by mountain climbers in general. In the Burangrang ? Tangkuban Perahu ? Bukit Tunggul ? Mount Manglayang mountain range, Mount Manglayang is the most beautiful mountain of the four mountains. Maybe that's why among outdoor activists, this mountain was forgotten except for outdoor activists from Bandung and its surroundings. Even so, Mount Manglayang still offers its own natural charm.

At Lembang Park & Zoo there are 370 animals, complete with various types of herbivores, carnivores and omnivores. The total area of this place is 20 hectares, but only 10 hectares has been developed. The rest will be developed as a tour with a safari concept. In the safari area, visitors can go around using vehicles to see animals that are free to be released in the area.

Place_Name: Traffic Park Ade Irma Suryani Nasution
Description: Ade Irma Suryani Traffic Park is a recreational park in the heart of Bandung, West Java, Indonesia. Aside from being a park and playground, here is also used as a training center for reading traffic signs. Traffic Park has the meaning that a traffic park or children's traffic park is a park where children can learn the rules of the road. A traffic park is also called a village transportation park or a traffic or safety park depending on the locale. Traffic parks are often created as an attraction within a larger park. In other cases, they are garden disposable and often on a small scale. They can be found in both urban and rural areas.

Lawangwangi is an art gallery with a modern retro concept. Blending natural beauty and culinary tastes. Hmm, makes me curious, Friend Traveler. Lawangwangi Creative Space previously only provided a Math Lab and Art Space for art lovers and connoisseurs. Visitors can find a special room to showcase creations from various artists. The works displayed vary each month. However, art galleries, which were initially predicted to attract many visitors, appear to be of less interest. Finally, by combining the natural beauty around the building, a modern cafe with an artistic feel was built.

Dago Waterfall, Bandung City, West Java, is located at an altitude of 800 meters above sea level with a waterfall reaching 12 meters high. This waterfall was formed as a result of the flow of the Cikapundung River which flows along the Maribaya area to the city of Bandung. Curug Dago expert Bandung has a high historical value with traces of history to the Kingdom of Thailand. The reason is that there is an inscription from the Kingdom of Thailand from the 18th century which reads the name of King Chulalongkom III or Rama V from the Kingdom of Thailand.

Kampung Korea is an area in the city of Bandung that was built as closely as possible with the character of the city of Seoul in South Korea. The purpose of developing this area is as part of sister city activities between Bandung and Seol. Construction began in 2017 at the initiative of Ridwan Kamil as the mayor of Bandung at that time. The existence of the Korean village was intended to increase tourism in the city of Bandung.

Kampung Batu Malakasari is a tourist spot that was founded in a former stone quarry. At that location, the carvings of former mining stones are still clearly visible. Now, the former stone quarry is filled with water which forms a lake. This tourist spot has the concept of educational, adventure and culinary tourism vehicles. Usually it is often used as a field trip destination for schools around Bandung. Various rides and facilities are very complete to support field trip programs for schools.

Not only enjoying the cool and green surroundings, your child can also take part in various useful educational activities. Various educational activities are provided and designed in such a way as to be attractive to families. The available educational activities are suitable for children from kindergarten to high school.

Curug Tilu Leuwi Opat is one of the tourist waterfalls in Lembang. The place itself is quite spacious. Here there are outbound areas, camping, and of course waterfall and river tours. The front area is a valley with a clear river. Usually outbound, camping and games are carried out in this area. The location of the Tilu Leuwi Opat waterfall is actually directly next door to Dusun Bambu, you know. Have you ever been to Dusun Bambu? if you go up the Lutung Kasarung skywalk, or visit the camping area, you can see the valley directly adjacent to the bamboo hamlet. Well, the valley is included in the Tilu Leuwi Opat tourist area. In this valley flows a river with clear water sourced from Situ Lembang.

Kiara Artha Park is an integrated area that combines iconic residential, business, commercial and tourist concepts in the city of Bandung with an area of + 2.9 hectares. Kiara Artha Park itself is one of the many public spaces with the theme of City Parks in Bandung, which is located in the center of the city of Bandung. This park complements other thematic parks that already exist in the city of Bandung. This city park has now become a tourist destination for Bandung residents in particular and for the general public. Even though this park just opened on August 17 2019, Bandung residents and the public are very enthusiastic about coming and enjoying the various activities and rides that are available.

NuArt Sculpture Park is a gallery owned by a well-known artist in Bandung named Nyoman Nuarta. Born in Tabanan Bali, Nyoman Nuarta finally settled in Bandung. And there is an interesting fact about this international-class artist, where he apparently graduated from the Faculty of Fine Arts from a well-known university in Bandung, namely ITB in 1979. Nyoman Nuarta's skills as a maestro sculptor and also a great sculptor are indeed well known internationally, therefore he created the NuArt Sculpture Park to showcase all the works of art he has so far.

Upside Down World Bandung first opened on October 10, 2016 with a very unique concept. All the furniture in the Upside Down World is installed upside down as if visitors were on the ceiling of the room. With the concept of the best home, this tourist spot has its own uniqueness. Visitors who come here are mostly young people who want to take pictures with an unusual background. Inside this building there are ten rooms with different themes just like in a house. There is a living room, children's bedroom, family room, lounge, kitchen, bathroom, and so on. Visitors can take pictures in all rooms and the photos can be printed at a photo printing service. If visitors feel unusual and confused about what style to take, then there will be an officer who can direct their style. Or by looking at the photos of previous visitors posted in that room.

Pesona Nirwana Waterpark is a 4000 square meter water rides attraction located in Legok Jeungjing Village, Panyirapan Village, Soreang District, Bandung Regency. It is about 1 Km from the Regional Government Office of Bandung Regency. This tourist location is open to the public every day and can be an alternative choice of tourist sites in Bandung Regency besides the Ciwidey tourist area. The Pesona Nirwana Waterpark location is a former mining area C with steep cliffs in most of its locations and is part of an environmentally friendly resort plan with the total development target is 4 hectares. The owner of Pesona Nirwana Waterpark is I Nyoman Nuarta, a sculptor from Bali who is also known as a figure in environmental preservation.

Relaxing weekend getaways are suitable for spending time in the park. One of the parks that can be a tourist destination is the Bandung Elderly Park. Elderly is an abbreviation for Elderly. Even so, this park is not specifically for the elderly, but for all groups. The name of the elderly is probably given because the age of this park is very old. In fact, it is hundreds of years old, because it has been around since 1885.

Kampoeng Tulip is one of the tourist attractions in Bandung whose location is filled with very beautiful tulip flowers. Tulip itself is a beautiful flower that is synonymous with the Country of Windmills, namely the Netherlands. If you want to see tulips, you don't have to go all the way to Holland. Instead, just go to the city of Bandung, you can meet him. This tourist location has many visitors, ranging from tourists in the city and outside the city.

Selasar Sunaryo Art Space (SSAS) is a space and non-profit organization that aims to support the development of practice and study of art and visual culture in Indonesia. Founded in 1998 by Sunaryo, SSAS actively organizes activities oriented towards public education. With direction & support from the Selasar Sunaryo Foundation, SSAS's main focus is on organizing contemporary art programs, through exhibitions, discussions, residencies & workshops. As a cultural center, SSAS organizes activities related to other artistic disciplines such as design, craft, performing arts, literature, architecture, and so on. In addition to displaying the permanent collection, SSAS also organizes solo or joint exhibitions featuring works by young and senior artists, from Indonesia and abroad.

Teras Cikapundung Bandung was previously a slum and neglected area which was successfully converted into a tourist spot. Cikapundung is a river that divides the city of Bandung which starts from the North Bandung area and empties into the Citarum River, South Bandung. Previously, this park was a gathering place for creative people such as artists in Bandung. There are several art galleries and a lot of food stalls in this place, until in the end it was abandoned and left dirty. Now the Cikapundung Terrace in Bandung has turned into a tourist spot open to the public with an ecological and urban concept. Various interesting facilities are available on the Cikapundung Terrace and can be used during recreation on this one tourist attraction. Equipped with a fish pond and lights, making this park very beautiful to visit at night. What's more, the lively atmosphere makes the visitors forget that this place was once nicknamed "a place where jinn throw away children".

Barli Museum is a museum located in the city of Bandung. This museum is dedicated to remembering and exhibiting the works of painter Barli Sasmitawinata. This museum was founded in 1990 and inaugurated in October 1992 by Soesilo Soedarman, Minister of Tourism, Post and Telecommunications at that time. Initially the museum was not open to the public. However, nowadays the museum can be visited by anyone. This museum is also the venue for various artistic activities such as fine art exhibitions, sales of works, discussions and workshops, training in ceramics and painting studios.

The Batu Kuda area is in the form of hills with beautiful pine forests. Located at an altitude between 1150 to 1300 meters above sea level, you can find the fresh mountains of Bandung here. Batu Kuda is under the direct supervision of Perhutani. This place used to be impressed as it is. But now it's much more organized. Usually, this place is a family tourist destination for local residents. But now, it is better known and visited by more tourists too.

The Bandung Lautan Api Monument is a monument that is a landmark of Bandung. This monument is 45 meters high, has as many as 9 sides. This monument has become one of the famous monuments in Bandung. This monument is the center of attention every March 23 to commemorate the Bandung Sea of Fire incident.

One of the museums that has become an icon of this city is the Gedung Sate Museum. The museum, which is located in the same building as the office of the Governor of West Java, was built during the colonial period by a Dutch architect, Johan Gerber. Inaugurated on December 8 2017 and carrying the 'Smart Museum', the Gedung Sate Museum is the first interactive museum in Indonesia. The concept provides an information guide about historic buildings using digital technology.

The West Java People's Struggle Monument (Monju) is a Museum of the History of the West Java People's Struggle, in Tatar Pasundan or Parahyangan. The monument was inaugurated by the Governor of West Java, Raden Nana Nuriana on August 23, 1995.

The Indonesian Postal Museum has existed since the Dutch East Indies era under the name Pos Telegraph and Telephone (PTT). In 1931 the PTT Museum was opened which is located in the lower right wing of the PTT Head Office Building, Jalan Cilaki, number 55, Bandung, (now number 73). Or to be precise in the east wing of the government center building for West Java Province which is more famous for Gedung Sate. On September 27, 1983, the Minister of Tourism, Post and Telecommunications inaugurated PTT to become the Indonesian Postal Museum. The museum's collection consists of postage stamps from Indonesia and various countries which are very historic, with a total of 131,000,000 stamps and 200 collections of equipment, namely in the form of package scales, stamp printing tools, securities, letter delivery vehicles, and others. etc. In addition to storing the postal relics in the exhibition room, the Museum also has a social center space which can be used for various activities.

Ciwangun Indah Camp or CIC is a recreation area with the concept of nature adventure and outbound. This place is located in Parongpong sub-district, West Bandung regency, next to the bamboo hamlet. With a natural backdrop of the forest under the foot of Mount Burangrang, CIC deserves to be a tourist destination. With a place that still maintains its natural beauty, several activities can be done at CIC. Activities suitable for doing at CIC are activities based on natural adventures. Here are some suitable activities to do at Ciwangun Indah Camp.

Wot Batu is an energy configuration that comes from Sunaryo's spiritual and transcendental journey. In an open space of ?ñ2000 m2 with a series of 135 +1, stones are planted and arranged conceptually and harmoniously. Sunaryo draws a line from the mountains around Bandung, and from that line he brings volcanic stones as a masterpiece medium that is timeless. Every carving, inlay, and shard is not the result of an effort to change stone, but to carve a record for a civilization ? a legacy from the 21st century for the future. Sunaryo created Wot Batu as a 'spiritual bridge' : the balance between the human soul and the physical form of life, as a link between the four elements of nature. In Wot Batu, earth, fire, water and wind speak to each other in harmony. Wot Batu conveys the idea of space and time ƒ?? an awareness of human existence in an infinite natural dimension.

Curug Batu Templek Bandung is a natural waterfall located in East Bandung City. Of the many natural waterfalls in Bandung, Curug Batu Templek is no less interesting because the scenery around it is filled with rocky cliffs. The history of Curug Batu Templek is very simple, only because in this place there used to be a stone quarry where there was a waterfall flow and it was known that the flow came from a river that was above the cliff so it was called Curug Batu Templek.

Bandung Cathedral Church, or St. Peter's Cathedral, is a church located on Jalan Merdeka, Babakanciamis, Sumurbandung, Bandung, Indonesia. The building was designed by Charles Prosper Wolff Schoemaker and is of late neo-Gothic architectural style. Viewed from above, the shape resembles a symmetrical cross. St. Peter's Cathedral has a land area of 2,385 mý and a building area of 785 mý. The church itself is named St. Franciscus Regis on June 16, 1895. After Bandung received gemeente (municipal level) status in 1906, it was decided to build a new church building. The construction of a new building was carried out in 1921. The cathedral was then blessed on 19 February 1922 by Mgr. Edmunds Luypen, SJ

The Wangsit Mandala Siliwangi Museum is a military museum located in the city of Bandung, West Java. Siliwangi is the name of the regional military command for the TNI-AD in West Java and Banten whose name is taken from the king of the Sunda Kingdom whose capital is Pakuan Pajajaran whose power is said to be unlimited, as well as wise and prudent and dignified in running the wheels of government. Meanwhile, the meaning of Mandala Wangsit is a place to store messages, advice or advice from past warriors to future generations through the objects they left behind. The museum was inaugurated by the commander of the Siliwangi division, Colonel Ibrahim Adjie, on May 23, 1966. The museum is located on Jalan Lembong, Sumurbandung district. This road is taken from the name of Lt. Col. Lembong, one of the Siliwangi soldiers who was a victim in the Coup Event of the Ratu Adil Armed Forces. Previously the street was called Oude Hospitaalweg.

Bandung never loses its charm, its natural attractions always seduce tourists to visit. Caringin Tilu is one of them, a tour with beautiful natural scenery. The view of the city of Bandung that stretches 180 degrees. The favorite place for tourists in this tourist area is Moko Hill. Where there are many cafes and places to eat that are ready to accompany tourists' relaxed holidays. During the day, beautiful natural scenery is presented, and at night it's time to be replaced by a view of the city lights.

Panama Park Bandung is one of the playgrounds in Bandung, West Java. This recreational vehicle, which is said to be the largest in Bandung, was opened in May 2019. There are several games offered in this arena, such as a playground to a snow park filled with snow. Users can also feel the sensation of real snow.

Angles of View Cafe Bandung is a new tourist destination in the Pluncut area. The Bandung Cafe Viewpoint itself is located in the Sarae Hills area on Jalan Pagermaneuh, RT 05/RW 07, Pagerwangi, Lembang, West Bandung Regency, West Java. For information, Sarae Hills is a tourist area in Punclut that combines natural tourism, culinary tourism, selfie tourism and outbound activities. In this area, you can vacation with friends or family while enjoying the natural scenery and Bandung city view. Previously, Sarae Hills had worked with several tourist attractions, namely Tafso Barn, Lereng Anteng, De BlankON, Dago Bakery, Cakrawala Sparkling Nature, and D'Dieuland. So, starting on September 5, Sarae Hills is decorated with a cafe which is none other than the Angles of View Cafe Bandung.

This Batu Kuda Camping Ground is located in Cibiru Wetan Village, Cileunyi District, Bandung Regency, precisely at the foot of Mount Manglayang. The Batu Kuda area itself is quite famous among the local community. Apart from being the first point for climbers who want to continue their journey to the top of Mount Manglayang, it is said that in ancient times, a prabu from a kingdom in West Java named Prabu Layang Kusuma was riding his horse which could fly around Mount Manglayang. And suddenly the horse ridden by the King fell into a puddle. No matter how hard the horse tries to get out of the puddle it doesn't work. Until gradually the horse belonging to the King who fell turned into stone. So the stone is called the Horse Stone. Apart from that, the King himself chose to meditate near Batu Kuda, and now the place where the King meditated is known as Batu Kursi. The Batu Kuda camping area is quite extensive, so you don't have to worry about running out of camping spots. Not only that, you can see towering pine trees as far as the eye can see. Apart from being used as a camping spot for climbers, you can also take your family on vacation. Because this area is open to you and your family who just want to take a walk to enjoy the pine forest, or spend the night sleeping in a star-studded hotel.

Bukit Bintang (Malay [bu.ket?? bi.nta?]; known as Bintang Walk or Starhill, the latter being the translation of the Malay name) is the name of a shopping and entertainment district in Kuala Lumpur, Malaysia. This area includes Jalan Bukit Bintang and the surrounding area. This area has long been Kuala Lumpur's most prominent retail hub which is home to many famous shopping malls, al fresco cafes, swanky bars, night markets as well as hawker-type restaurants. This area is popular with both tourists and locals, especially among the youth. A section of Bintang Walk is identically referred to as "Arab Street".

Vanda Bandung Park is a park located in the city of Bandung, West Java. This garden has a background view of the fountain at night. At night, fountains are installed at 20 points with dazzling colorful lights. To complement the people of Bandung who want to relax, Taman Vanda provides park benches. Lush trees planted around the garden make it fresher and more beautiful. Relaxing here during the day is also very fun with the breezy wind and sunlight covered by the thick trees.

West Java Cultural Park (TBJB) was established in 1991 in the Dago Tea House area. TBJB has the facilities of a closed theater building, open theater, exhibition hall, secretariat, arts studio, arts guesthouse, and cafeteria. All of these facilities are intended for the smooth activities and work of Bandung residents, especially artists. TBJB holds a variety of interesting agendas such as art performances, art competitions, artwork experimentation, seminars, workshops, art and cultural workshops, book publishing, etc.

Bugbrug Waterfall As the name implies, the word Bugbrug in Sundanese means overlapping or overlapping. So if you are asked why this waterfall in Bandung is called Curug Bugbrug then the answer is because the water that falls from top to bottom looks like it is piled up. And from the fall, a sound was heard at the bottom of the waterfall like ƒ??brugƒ??brug ƒ? so loud. The waterfall which is located at an altitude of 1,050 meters above sea level, has a height of 50 meters in height and a waterfall width of about 2 meters. This place is the center of hunting for tourists who vacation in Bandung.

Place_Name: Babakan Siliwangi City Forest Path Bandung
Description: The Babakan Siliwangi forest walk is a public facility in the form of an urban forest. This forest is an urban forest that is still active in the city of Bandung until now. It is strategically located in the Taman Sari area, close to the ITB campus and the zoo. This area has a cool nuance because it is dominated by shady trees. Wooden and iron bridges that are connected to each other around this area become a path to walk through the forest. Visitors can walk on a wooden bridge while enjoying the fresh air in this urban forest area.

Who says soaking in hot water has to spend a lot of money? West Bandung Regency has a solution for travelers who want to experience the benefits of genuine mountain hot springs without having to pay a fortune. Is Curug Cipanas Nagrak, a natural tourist attraction that offers natural hot spring baths. This hot spring is not even just a pool, but a natural waterfall in the middle of a plantation area. The spring flows swiftly into a small waterfall in the middle of green hills. Visitors will feel the sensation of soaking in a comfortable hot tub in the middle of nature.

Jomblo Park may refer to:

Pasupati Park, a park founded by Ridwan Kamil in Bandung
Pedestrian Jomblo, a recreational area established in Jambi
Single Park (Mataram), a park established in Mataram, West Nusa Tenggara

Bandung seems to never stop offering interesting tourist attractions to visit. Especially for young people. Some time ago the Map of Park Bandung was opened. Tourist attractions that offer the concept of clean and beautiful gardens. It is suitable as a place to relax and avoid the hustle and bustle of the city. This recreational park in downtown Bandung has the concept of a picnic park. Because of this, while here, visitors can not only take pictures. However, you can also do other activities such as having a picnic.

in July 1993 a three-story mosque was erected, to be precise at Jalan Gegerkalong Girang number 38 Bandung. This mosque is often dubbed as the mosque of a thousand hands because it was built in mutual cooperation by thousands of people and congregations of Daarut Tauhid. At that time, at the bottom of the Daarut Tauhid Mosque building a number of bedrooms were allocated which functioned as student dormitories for female students or sisters with a capacity of 70 people. The second and third floors are used for prayer, while the first floor is used as an area for shops (minimarkets), special rooms for sisters, ablution rooms, and bathrooms. In 2015, the construction of the expansion and renovation of the Daarut Tauhid Mosque in Bandung was carried out on a large scale. The laying of the first stone for the construction of the mosque was carried out on Thursday, 29 January 2015. Two years later, on 20 November 2017, the Daarut Tauhiid Mosque was completed and inaugurated by KH. Abdullah Gymnastiar as the Trustee of the Daarut Tauhiid Islamic Boarding School. The mosque as a result of the latest renovation was built with 4 floors plus a one-story basement. The door of the mosque is separated between brothers and sisters. DKM Front Office (FO) is also in each area. Place of ablution and bathroom close to the entrance. One of the things that distinguishes the Daarut Tauhid Mosque from others is that it is very friendly to people with disabilities, namely by facilitating a special elevator for them to make it easier for them to climb up to the 4th floor of the mosque. Apart from that, it is also equipped with special bathrooms for the disabled which are separated for brothers and sisters. .

Place_Name: Great Mosque of Trans Studio Bandung
Description: Trans Studio Bandung Grand Mosque (TSB) stands majestically. This 4,000 square meter Middle Eastern-style house of worship is an oasis amidst shopping centers and recreational areas. the concept of a modern mosque that adopts the Middle Eastern style is based on the direction of Chairul Tanjung (CT), as the owner of CT Corp. He immediately dreamed of realizing the design of the TSB Grand Mosque which is thick with the touch of the Nabawi Mosque.

The Indonesian Tiberias Church (GTI), or Tiberias Ministry is one of the Protestant Christian church synods in Indonesia. One of the hallmarks of GTI's ministry is the ministry of Divine Healing through Holy Communion and Anointing Oil. The Indonesian Tiberias Church is a revelation church that was ordered by the Lord Jesus to Pdt. Dr. Isaiah Pariadji. The task of the Tiberias Church is to prove that Jesus Christ is the Lord God Almighty through His miracles; that God's Word consists not in words, but in power; that the Word of God is more than all human knowledge; that humans must live in repentance, must live in holiness in order to be worthy of standing before Him and the feast in the Kingdom of Heaven.

Tektona Waterpark is a vehicle that gives the sensation of playing in the water with your family and friends, providing joy for both children and adult visitors with modern facilities including Wave Pool and Current Pool, Kids and Toddler Pool, Semi Olympic and Mini Slider for children and Mega Sliders for adults with a height of almost 30 meters, which will trigger the adrenaline of the visitors. Apart from that, the Tektona Waterpark rides also provide a culinary corner, a gazebo as well as pump services and action photos which can be obtained at the corner of the Tektona Waterpark rides, and changing rooms and rinse rooms are also always available within the Tektona Waterpark area.

Cilengkrang Waterfall can be a choice of natural tourist destinations in Bandung. It offers a cool forest area as well as a refreshing waterfall area. Even though it's not big, the waterfall area is capable enough to calm and refresh tourists. As if contrary to the frenetic city of Bandung. Cilengkrang Waterfall offers natural attractions that are calm and so green. Enchanting waterfalls, as well as forests with trees that are so beautiful. Where, this place is also a living habitat for various wild animals that are still awake.

Pasupati Bridge or Pasupati Flyover is a bridge that connects the northern and eastern parts of the city of Bandung through the Cikapundung valley. It is 2.8 km long and 30-60 m wide. Part of the road was built on Jalan Pasteur, which is an old road with palm trees on the right and left which characterizes the city of Bandung. The Pasupati Flyover is also one of the icons of the city of Bandung. Therefore, at night the center of the Pasupati Bridge is illuminated with colorful spotlights. This flyover makes traffic flow from the area around Jabodetabek to Bandung easier. Under the Pasupati Bridge there is a park called Pasupati Park.

Pasar Baru is a trading area centered on Jalan Pasar Baru, Pasar Baru Village, Sawah Besar District, Central Jakarta. This shopping center was founded in 1820, and is the oldest shopping center in Jakarta. The southern end of Jalan Pasar Baru is adjacent to Jalan Antara and Jalan Pasar Baru Selatan, as well as Jalan Pos which is adjacent to the Jakarta Art Building. The northern end of Jalan Pasar Baru is adjacent to Jalan Kyai Haji Samanhudi, near Metro Pasar Baru and Jalan Jalan Kimia Ayam. On the left and right sides of Jalan Pasar Baru there are clothing shops, textile and tailor shops, sporting goods and shoe shops, eyewear shops, and gold jewelery shops. Indian-Indonesians traded selling cloth, sporting goods, and shoes at Pasar Baru. In 2002 there were about 2,000 Indian families registered as residents of Jakarta, and most of them lived in the city center, particularly in the Pasar Baru and Pintu Air areas. In the Pasar Baru area there is also a place of worship for the Indian-Indonesian community.\n\n

Bandung Historical Park is a park located behind the Bandung City Hall, the Bandung City Government complex. This park serves to introduce history in the city of Bandung. This park is equipped with information about Bandung city leaders from time to time. The construction of this park spent a budget of around 3.5 billion rupiah.

Roemah Seni Sarasvati is a gallery located on Jl. General Sudirman 137, Bandung. RSS is the main project of Sarasvati Arts Management which was built with the aim of introducing a variety of cultural and artistic diversity. RSS is also a place to exchange ideas and concerns to create a unique identity for the city of Bandung and nurture creativity and knowledge. One of the work programs being designed is the Grote Postweg Art Project.

Puspa Science and Technology Sundial is an educational vehicle located in the Kota Baru Parahyangan area, Padalarang, Bandung, West Java. Puspa Science and Technology Sundial was inaugurated on May 11 2002, coinciding with the moment of National Education Day. The existence of Puspa Science and Technology Sundial is an important effort for the realization of Kota Baru Parahyangan as an Independent City with an educational perspective. Starting in 2013 the area of teaching aids at Sundial Science Center for Science and Technology was also expanded and the facilities were completed, in line with the increasing public interest and concern for the world of science and technology.

Salman ITB Mosque is a campus mosque located at Jalan Ganesha 7, Lebak Siliwangi, Coblong, Bandung City or right in front of the ITB Ganesha Campus area. With a land area of 7800 m2 and a mosque building area of 1225 m2, the Salman Mosque is equipped with various supporting facilities such as a canteen, free drinking water, mini market and function room. The mosque, which opened in 1972, is the first campus mosque in Indonesia.

Aseupan waterfall is in the Tilu Leuwi Opat waterfall area. This waterfall is the main star of several waterfalls here. If told, her beauty can fill galleries and Instagram feeds. This waterfall itself is located in Ciwangan Hamlet, Cihanjuang Rahayu Village, Parangpong District, West Bandung Regency. About 9 KM from Lembang which is rarely quite close to Cimahi Waterfall. Not only does it provide views of the waterfall, around the waterfall there is also a fairly large camping ground area.

The Indonesian Education University National Education Museum was inaugurated by the Governor of West Java, H. Ahmad Heryawan, Lc. The construction of the National Education Museum is one form of UPI's responsibility as a tertiary institution that has concern for the preservation of the nation's cultural historical heritage, especially in the field of education. Museums generally exhibit collections of objects from the past, but this is different from the National Education Museum at the Indonesian University of Education. This museum presents how education will be in the future, because now education is forecasting. The existence of the National Education Museum is expected to be able to become a vehicle for research centers, as well as learning and learning resources, which can increase the competence of educators and students' insights in seeking to improve the quality of education, as well as becoming a cultural tourism destination in West Java and National. Because basically humans don't study the past, but the future.

Bandung Indah Waterpark is one of the swimming pools in Bandung. Provides a variety of water games suitable for families. There is a swimming pool for adults and children. Visitors can do swimming and recreational sports.

Curug Anom is a waterfall that has rock walls or flat-shaped cliffs, so that at first glance it looks like a wall, even though this is actually a rock cliff that has a flat surface with a height of approximately 30 meters. The location of Curug Anom is in the area of the Natural Hill Lembang tourist attraction, precisely on Jln. Colonel Masturi, Kec. Cisarua, Kab. West Bandung, West Java. Even though the water discharge at Curug Anom Lembang is not very large, due to the very high size of the cliff, the splashes of water falling from above will feel like local rain. The stream of water that falls follows the flat surface of the cliff wall and then hits the bottom of the waterfall looks like a piece of silk cloth that adorns the rock wall.

This Rhinoceros Park was just inaugurated on December 19, 2017 by Mr. Ridwan Kamil as Mayor of Bandung. There is a rhino statue that is tens of years old in this park which has become its icon. The Rhinoceros statue was revitalized, so that now it has a new appearance and has become a favorite photo spot for visitors. Apart from the Rhinoceros Statue, there is also a Statue of Dewi Sartika next to the Rhinoceros Park which was also revitalized, but the statue of Dewi Sartika was initially small and has now been enlarged.

Film Park is one of the thematic parks and public open spaces in the city of Bandung which is located under the Pasupati Bridge, Bandung, West Java. This park was inaugurated by the Mayor of Bandung, Ridwan Kamil, on September 14 2014. This park has a modern open-air cinema concept so that residents can do their activities in the park and get facilities to watch movies for free. The film park is managed by the Bandung Film Community and the Bandung City Park Service.

The Nike Ardilla Museum was inaugurated or opened to the public on the day when Nike Ardilla, if he was still alive, was 21 years old. It was inaugurated directly by the family, namely his own father (deceased) R. Eddy Kusnaedi by cutting a birthday cake, and witnessed directly in front of the Nike Ardilla Fans Club community. This museum occupies a house building which will be a silent witness and store all Nike Ardilla's memories during his lifetime, and is also popularly known as the Nike Ardilla House (RNA). Traveler's friends, The basic concept of the Nike Ardilla (RNA) House building is a blend of designs that resemble Planet Hollywood, Hard Rock Cafe and Museums in general that we usually see. The Nike Ardilla Museum occupies a 2-storey building with an area of 500 square meters, where the first floor is used as the residence of the late Nike Ardila family. Meanwhile on the 2nd floor of the Museum, apart from being used as a display room for Nike Ardilla's collections, accessories and personal belongings, you can also see what private space looks like in the form of Nike Ardilla's room with everything in it.

The Batununggal swimming pool is one of the swimming pools that Bandung residents love when on vacation. The swimming pool is located in the Batununggal Insah Estate housing complex. For those of you who are familiar with housing, it's definitely easy to get to the location. This swimming pool is actually called Batununggal Indah Club Swimming Pool or BIC swimming pool. This swimming pool is one of the exclusive facilities for residential residents. Even though it is a residential facility, the management has opened it to the public. So for those of you who are in Bandung and its surroundings, without having to live in the housing, you can already enjoy your vacation there, friend.

Welcome to Mountain View Golf Club Dago Pakar Bandung. Golf Course with par 72, 18 holes has been designed by British 5 times world Champion Peter Thompson and of course famous achitect Ross Peret, located in a prestigious residential complex only 30 minutes from Bandung international airport or 20 minutes from city center. Golfers and visitors sitting in the front row will be presented with views of the Club House and the golf course in the mountains close to the city of Bandung. Equipped with world class facilities, complete with VIP rooms, Massage Room, Luxurious lockers for men and women, Champions Bar, Restaurant and Golf Shop adjacent to the lobby entrance.

Mount Lalakon is a mountain located in Jelegong Village, Badaraksa Village, Kutawaringin District, Bandung Regency, West Java and has a height of 870 meters. Mount Lalakon is famous for its shape which resembles a perfect cone or pyramid. Mount Lalakon is also known as Mount Sabelas because at the top of this mountain there are two PLN towers which when viewed from a distance form the number 11, this PLN tower is connected to the Saguling hydropower plant. So, for the safety of the tower and its functions, this is what makes the permits to this mountain a little tight. It's not surprising when you are approaching the top, lots of bamboo is stretched to the path with the aim of closing the hiking trail. , such as the Lawang Stone, Customary Stone, Warung Stone, Fertilizer Stone, Renges Stone, Elephant Stone, and a Long Stone which is located above the peak. According to one of the community leaders of Badaraksa Village, Abah Acu, "philosophically, Mount Lalakon is a symbol of a play from human life. The stones represent various professions (plays) chosen by humans."\nThe view from this mountain is quite good, all around The corner of Bandung Regency can be seen from the peak, including the view of the Saguling Reservoir to the west. Several sides of this mountain have been damaged by illegal excavation activities (excavation C), such as in the Cipatik area on the north side and the Situwangi area on the west side.

This area is located in RPH Cikalong Wetan, BKPH Padalarang Perum Perhutani BKPH North Bandung. Judging from the area, it reminds me of one of the tourist attractions in Central Java. More precisely, it is located in Klaten, the name is Umbul Ponggok. For Native friends who have been to Umbul Ponggok, this spring tourist attraction is almost exactly the same. It's just that, in this area it is used multi-purpose. Versatile means. The source of the spring that comes out of this tourist attraction is also used by some of the local community as a washing place. Wait a minute, don't feel disgusted just yet. The spring that produces this spring flows clean water almost every minute.

This lake has clear, greenish water that blends beautifully with the large rock cliffs around it. Between the rocks, you can find trees and green grass that are refreshing to the eye. The tall rocks are even often used as a place for travelers to jump beautifully to this ancient lake. Lake Sanghyang Heuleut has a depth of about three meters. So, before you enter the lake, make sure you can swim so you don't drown, or at least have equipment such as a life jacket.

Lereng Anteng Panoramic Coffee is a fun hangout place in the form of cafes and restaurants with a mix of cafes and natural tourist spots. This one eating place was opened on June 1 2016 and occupies an area of around 500 mý and comes with a cozy concept. The name of this cafe is taken from the word Slope, which means a place on the outskirts of a plateau, and Anteng (Sundanese) means a place with a comfortable atmosphere. Apart from serving a variety of food and drink menus, Lereng Anteng Panoramic Coffee also offers a view that is so incredibly beautiful

The PUSDAI Mosque (Islamic da'wah center) was built in original architecture in Indonesia, with the distinctive shape of the Limas roof. Apply it to all the roofs of the building by combining the architectural styles of mosques from all corners of the Islamic world. Unique than the others, it turns out that there is a dome (roof of the mosque) made of wood. Some of the ornaments in this mosque are made of wood and seem natural and so strong. Marble stone also dominates the mosque building with several ethnically patterned decorations in the calligraphy patterns found in the PUSDAI mosque building.

Al Imtizaj Mosque is one of the mosques with oriental nuances and architecture with a bamboo curtain pattern in the city of Bandung. The location of this mosque is more precisely located at Jalan Banceuy number 8, Bandung City, West Java.

Situ Cileunca, located in Warnasari, Pangalengan, Bandung, West Java, is an artificial lake with an area of up to 1,400 hectares with beautiful hills and mountains as a backdrop. Apart from functioning as a tourist attraction, Situ Cileunca also functions as a hydroelectric power plant (PLTA). The water that comes from the lake is channeled through the Palayangan River. This river is also often used as an arena for rafting. The depth of the lake reaches 17 meters, and before 1918, this was a wilderness which was later converted into a lake, which served to serve the community's water needs.

Sunrise Point Cukul is one of the popular tourist spots for tourists to see the sunrise in the South Bandung area. They can see the sunrise from a height of 1,600 meters above sea level. Sunrise Point Cukul is one of the popular tourist spots for tourists to see the sunrise in the South Bandung area. They can see the sunrise from a height of 1,600 meters above sea level.

The Palayangan River is located in the Situ Cileunca Pangalengan Tourism Object Area, Kab. Bandung, about 45 Km or approximately 2 hours drive from the center of Bandung City. This is the most popular Rafting location in the South Bandung area because it has several advantages compared to other rivers. Here are the advantages of Rafting on the Palayangan River:

One of the well-known tea plantations in West Java is the Malabar tea plantation which was built during the Dutch colonial period in 1896. This plantation is included in the Pangalengan sub-district, Bandung Regency, approximately 45 km from the center of Bandung City. If you visit this area, your eyes will be spoiled by the activities of the local population, where the majority of the population work as tea pickers and raise dairy cows. So don't be surprised if you enter this area, you will see residents picking tea gardens and raising cows. However, to reach the Malabar plantation in Pangalengan, you have to take a long and winding journey, so you have to be careful.

In Subang, there is the Ciater Hot Spring area which is often the target of tourists. This tourist area which is open 24 hours has a water temperature of around 43-46 degrees Celsius. It is suitable for refreshing the body of tourists. There are various hot spring pools here. Both for adults and children. The water temperature in the children's pool is limited to 39 degrees Celsius, while the adult pool can reach 46 degrees Celsius.

Bosscha Observatory is one of the oldest star observation sites in Indonesia. The Bosscha Observatory (formerly known as Bosscha Sterrenwacht) was built by the Nederlandsch-Indische Sterrenkundige Vereeniging (NISV) or the Dutch East Indies Star Association. The Bosscha Observatory is located in Lembang, West Java, about 15 km to the north of the city of Bandung with geographic coordinates 107ø 36' East Longitude and 6ø 49' South Latitude. This place stands on 6 hectares of land, and is located at an altitude of 1310 meters above sea level or at an altitude of 630 m from the Bandung plateau. The observatory code of the International Astronomical Union for the Bosscha observatory is 299. In 2004, the Bosscha Observatory was declared a Cultural Heritage Object by the Government. Because of that the existence of the Bosscha Observatory is protected by Law Number 2/1992 concerning Cultural Heritage Objects. Furthermore, in 2008, the Government established the Bosscha Observatory as one of the national Vital Objects that must be secured.

Cihideung Flower Garden has a simple natural charm but is able to produce a landscape that grabs attention. The charm of this garden / flower garden is only limited to a type of flower plant. Then there are also several other attractions that make this natural tourist destination included in the Bandung tourist list. One of them is the photo spot area which is very contemporary and instagramable which is the main target of teenage tourists. Especially for influencers who are looking for the perfect backdrop for content.

The Lodge Maribaya is one of the tourist attractions in Lembang that offers various things to visitors. Here we can do various activities such as camping, trekking around the beautiful pine forest area, gathering and team building events, or even just refreshing to enjoy culinary delights. There are also various rides which are definitely very instagrammable. Surrounded by mountains with distinctive pine forests, the air and atmosphere here are really fresh. Want to hold a private gathering, or even a wedding here? really can. With a beautiful green mountain backdrop, of course, it will make your event more memorable.

Forest Park Ir. H. Djuanda (Tahura Djuanda) is a conservation area that is integrated between secondary nature and plantation forests of the Pinus type (Pinus merkusil) located in the Cikapundung River Sub-Watershed and the Citarum Watershed which stretches from Curug Dago, Dago Pakar to Curug Maribaya which is part of the Pulosari Mountain forest group. Tahura Djuanda is located in the north of Bandung City, approximately 7 km from the city center, geographically located at 1070 30' East Longitude and 60 52' South Latitude, administratively it is in the area of Ciburial Village, Cimenyan District, Bandung Regency and partly belongs to the Village Mekarwangi, Cibodas Village, Langensari Village, and Wangunharja Village, Lembang District, West Bandung Regency and Dago Village, Coblong District, Bandung City.

Bandung Begonia Garden is located at an altitude of 1200 meters above sea level. Apart from Balinea, there are various other types of flowers such as salvia, impatiens, geraniums and celosia. So beautiful that many people call it the equivalent of the Himawari no Sato park in Japan. The Balinea flower itself is a type of Begonia flower originating from Bali. Plants that are suitable for planting in various weather conditions will grow throughout the season. Balinea flowers are plants that are often planted in plantations and hotel grounds as well as city parks. The specialty of the Begonia Flower Garden is not only the presence of flowers and plants, but also an attractive garden arrangement. The colorful flower garden is also equipped with various shapes that are suitable for taking pictures. In fact, many visitors come here just to capture the beauty of the park. In addition, because it is located in the highlands, visitors will definitely be comfortable doing activities there with cool and refreshing temperatures.

The name Punclut may be quite familiar to tourists. The highland area in Bandung has recently become popular as a tourist destination. Besides offering beautiful scenery, this area also has many tourist attractions for recreation. One of them is the tourist area as well as the restaurant Tafso and Boda Barn or often known as Tafso Barn. This recreation area combines dining with a unique garden and warehouse feel. Views of the hills cut by the horizon line are the main target of visitors. It is perfect to hang out and relax while on vacation in Bandung.

Around Bandung, there are lots of waterfalls from the current ones, forgotten, not heard of until just heard of. One of them is the Luhur Cibodas waterfall in the Maribaya Lembang area around this area there are 3 waterfalls, the local people call it the Cibodas waterfall. again the highest waterfall in this area is Luhur waterfall.. the position is even deeper, about 3 km from the entry post, there are still very few people going there

Curug Malela is one of the natural destinations in the form of a waterfall. This waterfall has extraordinary beauty. So it's no wonder that many visitors come to visit this waterfall. The visitors who come are not only from within the city, but also from outside the city such as DKI Jakarta, Central Java, West Java and many more. This waterfall has a fairly high height, which is around 60 to 70 meters. However, this waterfall has a fairly narrow width, which is only about 50 meters. This towering waterfall has very heavy and cold water. So if you stand near this waterfall, be prepared for your clothes to get wet with splashes of water. Malela Waterfall does not only consist of one shower, but consists of several adjacent showers. Because this waterfall has showers that line up like Niagara Falls in America, many visitors call it "Cianjur's Niagara".

Curug Cimahi is a waterfall located on Jalan Colonel Masturi, Kertawangi Village, Cisarua District, West Bandung Regency, West Java. With a height of about 87 meters, this waterfall is one of the highest waterfalls in Bandung and its surroundings. The name Cimahi comes from the name of the river that flows over it, namely the Cimahi River, which originates in Situ (lake) Lembang and flows into Cimahi City. This tourist destination is approximately 10 kilometers from Cimahi City in the direction of Lembang or 20 kilometers from Bandung City.

Situ Patenggang or Situ Patengan is a lake located in the natural tourist area of South Bandung, West Java, Indonesia, to be precise in Ciwidey. Located at an altitude of 1600 meters above sea level, this lake has very exotic views. Situ Patenggang also has beautiful natural scenery, because there are tea gardens around it. The area of Situ Patenggang is around 45,000 hectares. And the total area of the nature reserve reaches 123,077.15 hectares. Situ patenggang is always the choice of tourists, especially for those who have just returned from the White Crater tourist spot. The distance from the white crater tour is only about 7 KM and takes about 10 minutes.

The South Bandung area, especially Ciwidey, is already known as a natural tourist destination with beautiful panoramas and cool air, that's why urban people choose to travel to Ciwidey to "escape" themselves from their busy lives in the city. This Ciwidey tour is no less exotic than the White Crater, Rancaupas or Situ Patenggang. Based on historical records of Rengganis Crater, this crater was formed as a result of natural processes millions of years ago. Where based on research, Rengganis Crater was formed from the enormity of the eruption of Mount Sunda Purba, especially Mount Patuha, which also created another crater, Kawah Putih. We can see the evidence of the awesomeness of the eruption for ourselves, where until now in Rengganis Crater there is still a very strong smell of sulfur from the crater area.

Cimanggu Hot Spring is one of the tourist attractions in Bandung that offers a variety of attractions that are guaranteed to be amazing. This tourist spot is also known as Cimanggu Natural Hot Spring. Enjoying hot springs and also the green scenery in this bath can certainly make your mind more relaxed. A relaxed mind will definitely make you more excited when you get back to work.

Glamping Lakeside Rancabali offers a luxurious camping spot that is suitable for you to make a weekend getaway. As the name suggests, glamping or glamor camping consists of tents containing comfortable beds, indoor bathrooms, heaters, and various amenities like a five-star hotel. Located on Jalan Raya Ciwidey Rancabali KM 1, Glamping Lakeside is in the vicinity of Situ Patenggang and lush tea plantations. It's no wonder that the view from glamping is so beautiful and Instagramable for taking pictures.

Ciwidey Mushroom Hill is one of the many natural tourist charms located in Ciwidey District, Bandung Regency, West Java Province. Ciwidey Mushroom Hill does have a typical Ciwidey tour, which is a tourist attraction in the middle of a stretch of tea gardens, with very cool air. The atmosphere when the fog falls over the plantation area makes the atmosphere romantic. The atmosphere at Bukit Mushroom Ciwidey is also suitable for single people, there are many spots with beautiful natural backgrounds, where it is possible to forget your ex.

Sari Alam Medicinal Plant Garden is better known as herbal medicine tourism, because there are lots of plants used as alternative medicine. Sari Alam Medicinal Plant Garden is better known by Bandung people as KTO Sari Alam. Location: Jl. Raya Ciwidey bandung km 26 no 8 rt 1 rw 2 village Andir, Cukangenteng, Kec. Pasirjambu, Bandung district, West Java 40972

Natural and educational tourism objects have mushroomed lately. Apart from De Ranch and Lembang Farmhouse, there is also Happy Farm Ciwidey in Bandung. This tourist attraction is still relatively new, because it was only established in June 2019. The concept is almost the same, nature tourism and animal husbandry with educational elements. It is suitable to be a family tourist destination, especially for children. And it's even more exciting because playing in an outdoor area with cool air.

Saung Angklung Udjo (SAU) is a place that is a place for performances, a center for handicrafts made of bamboo, and workshops for musical instruments made of bamboo. In addition, SAU has a goal as an educational laboratory and learning center to maintain Sundanese culture and especially angklung. Founded in 1966 by Udjo Ngalagena and his wife Uum Sumiati, with the intention of preserving and maintaining traditional Sundanese art and culture. Located on Jalan Padasuka 118, East Bandung, West Java, Indonesia. With an atmosphere of fresh air and surrounded by bamboo trees, from bamboo handicrafts and bamboo interiors to bamboo musical instruments. Besides regular performances every evening, Saung Angklung Udjo has repeatedly held special performances which are held in the morning or afternoon. The show was not limited to being held at the location of Saung Angklung Udjo, but various invitations appeared in various places both at home and abroad, in August 2000 at Sasana Budaya Ganesha ITB, Bandung, Saung Angklung Udjo held a collaboration concert with young singers who nicknamed the Shirley Temple of Indonesia, namely Sherina. Saung Angklung Udjo is not limited to selling only performing arts, various products of traditional bamboo musical instruments (angklung, arumba, calung and others) are made and sold to buyers.

The Cihanjuang Butterfly Park in Bandung seems to have added to the list of unique and interesting tourist attractions in Bandung, such as the Jendela Alam Bandung theme park, as well as having very high educational value for children and as a learning tool for our children that the preservation of rare and beautiful animals This can be taught from an early age. And in fact, even though it is still relatively new, this family tourist spot in Bandung has in fact succeeded in attracting the attention of local tourists from the city of Bandung and tourists from outside the area who are on vacation in Bandung. The location of the tourist spot which is still very shady and cool, is supported again by the interior design of the butterfly garden which is laid out in a very detailed and attractive way. When traveling to this one tourist area, it is hoped that your children will be able to get information about how the process of metamorphosis of a butterfly starts from the seedling larva to growing up perfectly.

One of the bustling tours in Bandung is the Train Miniature Park which is in the Floating Market Lembang tourist park. By presenting complete and very detailed railroad knick-knacks, this miniature train park seems to really come alive. It is not surprising that this tourist attraction invites thousands of people to enjoy and learn a lot about railways both in Indonesia and the world. This miniature park provides a gift shop that sells various types of miniature vehicles ranging from cars, planes and trains, of course. In addition, visitors who want to enjoy a variety of culinary offerings can go directly to the Lembang Floating Market. For visitors who come from out of town can stay at hotels adjacent to the location of the miniature park. The distance from the hotel to the miniature park is around 200 meters to 1 kilometer. These hotels include the Grand Hotel Lembang, Cemara Asri Hotel, Buah Sinuan Hotel and Pesona Bamboe Hotel. Hotel rental rates for overnight stays are between Rp. 200,000 to Rp. 1,000,000.

Pawon Cave is a natural cave and ancient site located in Gunung Masigit Village, Cipatat District, Padalarang, West Bandung Regency, or about 25 km west of Bandung City. It is an important place for the Sundanese because it is where the Sundanese elders who now occupy the western part of the island of Java gather. There, an ancient human skeleton was found there which is said to be the ancestor of the Sundanese people (still being studied at the Bandung Archaeological Center).

Gantole Hill Cililin or also known as Venue Gantole is a tourist area which was originally opened for the purpose of holding the 2010 West Java Porda and the 2016 National Sports Week Paragliding. This tourist area became a byword after hosting the 2016 PON. Paragliding itself is a type of sport that is carried out on hillsides or mountains by only utilizing wind as the main source. Therefore the location of Cililin Gantole Hill which is at an altitude of 1063 masl with strong winds is perfect for this sport.

Bandros or Bandung Tour Bus is a tour bus operating in Bandung, West Java, Indonesia. Used by tourists in the city of Bandung. The bus was inaugurated by Mayor of Bandung Ridwan Kamil on New Year's Eve 2014, and on February 18 2018 it was announced that the tour bus would serve the city of Bandung. A local tour leader will accompany tourists on the bus. Bandros is managed by two parties: the Bandung Transportation Agency (which is related to the Regional Revenue and Expenditure Budget) and Mang Dudung which is part of Corporate Social Responsibility. The bus has a capacity of 22 people. There are six buses operated by the Corporate Social Responsibility division, and 12 buses operated by the Regional Revenue and Expenditure Budget which are managed by the BLUD UPT Bandung City Transportation Service.
