Kyotoku Floating Market Bandung, a contemporary tour that carries the theme of Japanese things. In this place you will see typical Japanese buildings and views like in the land of Sakura. Japan is one of the countries besides South Korea which is a favorite destination for tourists from Indonesia. Because it is already a developed country, visiting Japan requires a lot of accommodation costs, plane tickets, and a complicated visa processing process. You don't need to go far abroad, you can enjoy traveling with Japanese nuances in Bandung. The tour manager designed this place to be similar to Kyoto, an area in Japan that is thick with culture. You don't have to wait for April to see the cherry blossoms, which are a Japanese icon. This tourist area is decorated with cherry blossoms so that the Japanese atmosphere feels even thicker. For those of you who are interested in taking pictures wearing kimono or yukata with a Japanese-style background, fortunately they are displayed on Instagram. The following is a brief review of this tourist area.

Rainbow Garden Harapan Indah is one of the recreational parks especially suitable for families. With an 'eat and play' concept, Rainbow Garden Bekasi combines a children's play area with culinary tours. Various rides and activities are available in this colorful 3000 m2 tourist park.

Very interesting destinations with European nuances complete with public facilities that make you feel as if you are in Europe. There are hospitals, police stations, telephone boxes, roadside cafes, and other classic buildings. Still in the same complex as the Floating Market, this tourist spot presents classic European architecture that is so thick, you are guaranteed to be reluctant to leave.

Besides being popular because it has beautiful scenery and cool weather, Bandung also offers many creative tourist destinations. City parks, museums, and places to eat are not spared from the uniqueness and appeal of each. One of them is Little Seoul Bandung which is in the Chingu Caf‚ area. The outdoor area at this cafe is transformed to resemble the atmosphere of Dongdaemun Street in Seoul, South Korea. Without having to fly all the way to Ginseng Country, visitors can feel the atmosphere of Seoul here.

Gedong Songo Temple (Javanese: ˆ??ˆ??ˆ??ˆ? ˆ??ƒ??ˆ?'ˆ?¬ˆ? ˆ?§ˆ??ˆ? ƒ??ˆ?ñˆ?", translit. Candi Gedhong Sanga) is the name of a complex of Hindu cultural heritage temple buildings located in Candi village, Bandungan District, Semarang Regency, Central Java, Indonesia to be precise on the slopes of Mount Ungaran. In this temple complex there are nine temples. This temple was discovered by Raffles in 1804 and is a relic of Hindu culture from the 9th century Syailendra Dynasty (927 AD). This temple is located at an altitude of about 1,200 m above sea level, so the air temperature here is quite cold (ranging from 19-27 ?øC). The location of the nine temples scattered on the slopes of Mount Ungaran has beautiful natural scenery. In addition, this tourist attraction is also equipped with hot springs from springs containing sulfur, camping areas, and horseback riding tours.

The people of Central Java may already be familiar with the name "Puri Maerokoco". This tourist park is the Central Javanese version of "Taman Mini" which presents replicas and miniatures of typical buildings from various regions in Central Java. Currently, Puri Maerakaca has changed its name to Grand Maerakaca. With more varied rides, this recreational park is one of the tourist destinations in Semarang which is suitable for family recreation.

Kampung Pelangi or in English is called Rainbow Village is a designation for areas or villages where the houses of the people are painted in colorful colors. Actually Kampung Pelangi was originally a slum area which was creatively transformed into an attractive area to serve as a tourist destination, especially for people who are happy or looking for an interesting spot to capture the moment. Many areas in Indonesia, especially in Java have places called Kampung Pelangi, among others, in Malang, Semarang, Jakarta, Bandung, and other cities. An example of a village like this is the colorful village in Jodipan and Tridi, Malang City, East Java.

Lawang Sewu ("Thousand Doors") (Javanese: ˆ?ˆ??ˆ? ƒ??ˆ?ñˆ?§ˆ??ˆ??, translit. Lawang S??wu) is a landmark in Semarang, Central Java, Indonesia , which was built as the headquarters of the Dutch East Indies Railway Company. The colonial-era building is notorious as a haunted house and filming location, although the Semarang city government has been trying to change that image.

Sam Poo Kong (Chinese: ; pinyin: SŽ nb€?o D?ýng), also known as Gedung Batu Temple, is the oldest Chinese temple in Semarang, Central Java, Indonesia. Originally founded by the Chinese Muslim explorer Zheng He (also known as Sanbao), it is now shared by Indonesians of various religious denominations, including Muslims and Buddhists, and ethnicities, including Chinese and Javanese.

Nature tourism is in the spotlight for the world of tourism. Nature tourism is not only mountains, lakes, forests, waterfalls or beaches. But it also penetrates into rural concepts, such as the Kalipancur Valley Tourism Village. This tourist spot offers recreation with a rural concept in the city of Semarang. Even though it has a rural concept, the location is not far from the city center. And this long-standing tourist attraction is still in great demand by tourists.

Initially the Tinjomoyo Semarang (SMG) forest tourism park was a zoo with a variety of forest animals in it. However, there was a big flood, which cut off the big bridge which became the main access to the tourist forest. The Tinjomoyo Forest itself has an area contour with a mix of hills, rivers and forests. The most abundant plants here are teak and pine trees. Therefore, it's no wonder that this area is very suitable to be used as an unspoiled tourism forest. With a land area of 57.5 hectares, the area is more often used as a camping site.

Kasmaran Park is located to the left of the Flower Market. The food court building and Taman Kasmaran are built on two floors. The lower floor is used as a culinary spot, while the upper floor is a garden. Not just an ordinary park, Kasmaran Park is equipped with a very interesting view against the backdrop of Kampung Pelangi. Kasmaran Park is quite spacious, equipped with cafe-style chairs and tables. This new location is believed to be the newest selfie alternative spot in Semarang City.

visit Baruna Beach in Semarang City, Central Java! This one beach will provide a different tourist experience. The reason is, here there is no stretch of sand. Indeed, Baruna Beach is an 'unofficial' tourist attraction belonging to the City of Semarang. This beach is behind the cement factory area. So there is no density of tourists or surfing spots here. There is only a stretch of meadows and weeds in front of the calm Java Sea.

Marina Beach (Javanese: ˆ?ˆ?ñˆ??ˆ?ñˆ??ˆ??ƒ??ˆ??ˆ?®ˆ??ˆ??, translit. Marina Beach) is one of the tourist attractions beach located in the city of Semarang, Central Java. This beach holds exotic views typical of the city of Semarang. Previously, this place was a mangrove forest and ponds, but the local government turned it into a recreation area by way of land reclamation. The results of the reclamation from this mangrove forest are now in the form of housing, shops and offices, on the south coast.

Kampoeng Djadhoel is located in Semarang Batik Village, precisely in Kampung Batik Tengah RT 04/ RW 02, Rejomulyo Village, East Semarang District. The naming of Kampoeng Djadhoel was initiated on December 18 2016 by Ignatius Luwiyanto (50), a resident of Kampung Batik Tengah. Indonesian history is the background for the naming of Kampoeng Djadhoel.

The location of Taman Indonesia Kaya, which is in the center of Semarang city, allows this 5,000 square meter park to function as a place for the arts community of Central Java artists. Here there was a Culture Stage built with two sides that were all usable. Then there is Pandawa Lima Park which was made by Komroden Haro, Court of Art Connoisseurs, Amphitheater, Green Area, Gate Mural by five young Semarang artists, and not to forget the Dancing Fountain. This Dancing Fountain was built by the Semarang City Government which can move to the strains of classical music and Indonesian struggle songs. The Dancing Fountain is scheduled to light up daily from 19.00 - 20.00 and until 21.00 on weekends.

In recorded history, this place used to be a gas station area that didn't sell well. The former gas station was completely overhauled into a park. That said, the 600 square meter land area was renovated into a park with funds of around Rp. 1.8 billion. Pandanaran Park is located at Jalan Pandanaran, Mugassari, South Semarang. To be precise, it is at the junction between Jalan Pandanaran and Jalan MH. Thamrin. Unfortunately, getting parking here is quite difficult. Some visitors even have to park their vehicles in front of food stalls around the park.

The beginning of the establishment of the Agung Giri Natha Temple was inseparable from the presence of Hindus from various regions who began to arrive and settle in Semarang. Before settling down, Hindus in Semarang initially came to work and seek knowledge. Around 1967/1968 Hindus in Semarang proposed to the Semarang government to build a place of worship. Because previously Hindus when carrying out prayers were located from house to house. Agreeing with this proposal, the Semarang government finally gave a choice of various locations that were appropriate and suitable for the construction of a holy place, namely a temple.

Semarang mangrove forest tourism is almost never empty of tourists. Not infrequently visitors who come to this beautiful tour either take selfies or just walk up the wooden walkways. This object is also instagramable and suitable for sharing on social media, in fact it is much sought after by those who work in the field of photography.

Cipta Beach is also known as Petikemas Beach, because of its distance and location close to Petikemas Beach. Tourist attractions in Semarang Cipta Beach only has a small stretch of sand and is dominated by rocks. Cipta Beach is a favorite tourist destination for Semarang residents because it has a unique landscape and surrounding environment. Taking selfies is the main activity on the beach because there are many interesting spots that can be captured. On weekends or long holidays, tourists often flock to Cipta Beach to just see the beach views. However, this Cipta beach has calm waves, so it is safe to use for swimming. On Cipta Beach itself there are many weeds that add to the beautiful scenery and become a paradise for selfie hunters. The presence of thatch is what attracts visitors to come to Cipta beach just to take selfies.

This contemporary tourist destination is indeed on the rise in many cities, including Semarang. One of them is the Old City 3D Trick Art Museum, a museum with the theme of 3D Art which offers a different sensation from the usual museums. Because in it are exhibited various attractive 3-dimensional works of art for taking pictures. This tourist destination is still busy with visits because it continues to innovate. Every 3 months, the management will change the theme or installation of the artwork so that visitors can come many times without getting bored.

GPIB Immanuel Semarang (popularly known as Blenduk Church, sometimes spelled Blendug Church, and often pronounced mBlendhug) (Javanese: ˆ?'ˆ?¨ˆ?§ˆ??ƒ??ˆ??ˆ??ˆ? ˆ?¬ˆ??ˆ??ˆ? ˆ??ˆ? ˆ??, translit. Gr‚ja Blendhuk) is the oldest Christian church in Central Java built by the Dutch who lived in the city in 1753, with an octagonal shape ( eighth square). This church is actually called GPIB Immanuel Church, on Jl. Lt. Gen. Suprapto 32. The dome is large, covered in bronze, and inside is a Baroque organ. The architecture inside is based on the Greek cross. The church was renovated in 1894 by W. Westmaas and HPA de Wilde, who added two towers to the front of the church. The name Blenduk is a nickname from the local community which means dome. This church is still used every Sunday. Around this church there are also a number of other buildings from the Dutch colonial period.

One of the landmarks in the Kota Lama area of Semarang, Srigunting Park during the Dutch colonial era took the form of a plein parade for a parade stage, now it is an open space in the form of a park which is a place for community gatherings or activities. Srigunting Park is located on Jalan Letjen Suprapto 32 Kota Lama area, on the south side there is the Marba Building, on the southwest there is the Jiwasraya Building, on the west side there is the Blenduk Church and on the east side there is the Kerta Niaga Building. This park underwent renovations several times, such as in 2001 and 2004. In 2001, Srigunting Park was returned to its function as an open roar for recreation, after previously being a passive park. In 2004 the renovation of this park by making access on each side, until there are four entrances. And in the middle, a four-pronged lamppost was made to illuminate the four sides of the entrance.

You can find one of the arts-related tours in Semarang in the Old Town area, namely the Semarang Contemporary Art Gallery or more easily referred to as Galsem which means the Semarang Gallery. Semarang Gallery is one of the most well-known art museums and is still very popular among tourists, especially art lovers. The works of art exhibited here are the result of the cold hands of reliable artists from all over the archipelago.

The Sidomukti pennant tourist area is one of the Mountain Nature Tourism in Semarang, located in Sidomukti Village, Bandungan District, Semarang Regency. This tourist area is supported by facilities & services: Outbound Training, Adrenaline Games, Natural Swimming Park, Camping Ground, Pondok Wisata, Pondok Lesehan, and Meeting Room.

SALOKA is present as the largest recreational park in Central Java which is included in the list of Pesona Indonesia tourist destinations, and carries the concept of local wisdom based on the folk legend of Baru Klinthing.

Located about 2 KM from Ungaran City or about 18 KM from Semarang City, the Penggaron Tourism Ecotourism Area is administratively located in Susukan Village, Ungaran District, Semarang Regency. This area is one of the guided forests of the Mandiri Tourism, Seeds and Other Business Unit (KBM WBU I) of Central Java Perum Perhutani Unit I. Penggaron Tourism Ecotourism or Penggaron Nature Tourism Penggaron Tourism Forest is a forest tourism destination that you can use for a vacation with your family, one of which is for camping. This place is often used as a place for camping or vacation by the people of Semarang. Penggaron Tourism Ecotourism is an exotic forest, unfortunately this paradise in the city of Semarang is rarely touched by the eye. For visitors who ask the ticket window guard, with a simple answer and what it is "an ordinary forest that is often used for camping, nothing special", of course they will feel disappointed.

The Safinatun Najah Mosque or what visitors usually call it the Kapal Semarang Mosque is now a religious tour that is crowded with visitors during the month of Ramadan. The mosque which is located at Jalan Kyai Padak, Podorejo, Kec. Ngaliyan, Semarang City began to be crowded with visitors just before breaking the fast. Generally the main goal of those who come here is to worship, besides that there are also those who hunt for photos and culinary delights around the mosque area.

Semarang Tourism offers a variety of interesting tourist attractions. One of them is visiting the Celosia Flower Garden Bandungan. The location is at the foot of Mount Ungaran, Semarang. Offering views of the natural surroundings with panoramic views of the Ungaran mountains is the main attraction of this recreational park. Once you get here, the large parking area immediately welcomes you and you don't miss the welcome gate. Along the way to the ticket booth, there is a giant colorful pencil-shaped fence. In addition, around the fence there are colorful flowers that adorn the way to the entry counter.

Kali Pancur Getasan is a natural tourist area. Kali Pancur Waterfall is located in Nogosaren Village, Getasan District, Semarang Regency, about 14 km west of Salatiga City. To go to the location of this tourist attraction there is no public transportation, so you have to bring your own vehicle.

Chrysanthemum Gemah Ripah Village Tourism in Clapar Hamlet, Duren Village, Bandungan District, Semarang Regency can be an alternative vacation. In this place lies a charming colorful flower garden. It is a tourist complex of various varieties of chrysanthemum plantations. There are at least 20 varieties developed by the Gemah Ripah Farmers Group in the last two years. And this object began to be opened to the public as a tourist destination on November 6 2016. On a terraced area of about 12 hectares, you will be invited to tour the chrysanthemum flower garden specifically for tourist visits in an area of 6.5 hectares. There are at least 3 gardens prepared by the manager for visitors.

Rawa Pening (pening is a Javanese variant of the word "wening" which means quiet, calm, peaceful) (Javanese: ˆ?®ˆ??ƒ??ˆ?ˆ?¬ˆ??ˆ??ˆ? , translit. Rawa Pening) is a natural lake in Semarang Regency, Central Java. With an area of 2,670 hectares, it occupies the districts of Ambarawa, Bawen, Tuntang and Banyubiru. Rawa Pening is located in the lowest basin of the slopes of Mount Merbabu, Mount Telomoyo and Mount Ungaran. This lake is shallow and becomes the headwaters for the Tuntang River.

Maron Beach (Javanese: ˆ?ˆ?ñˆ??ˆ?ñˆ??ˆ??ƒ??ˆ??ˆ?®ˆ?§ˆ??ˆ??ˆ??, translit. Pasisir Maron) which is located to the west of Semarang, to be precise around the mouth of the Silandak River, can be reached from two places, namely from Ahmad Yani Airport or from Graha Padma Housing Complex, Krapyak. Approximately 3 km from the highway we can reach the location. If using a vehicle can be reached in about 10 minutes. However, if you want to walk, it can take 30 minutes from the end of the Graha Padma housing complex. Marone Beach. It is not clear who manages Maron Beach. What is clear is that every time we enter Maron beach, we only need to pay 2 thousand rupiahs, for parking fees. If you visit Maron Beach on Saturday afternoons, Sunday mornings, Sunday afternoons, or holidays, you can be sure there are many tourists from the Semarang area and outside the city. It can even be said that they are not inferior to the number of tourists in Parangtritis, Yogyakarta or Kuta, Bali. Almost every corner of the beach and beachside stalls are full of visitors.

For those of you who are confused about where to go for recreation in Semarang, just go to Water Blaster Semarang. Waterpark that provides lots of exciting games and attractions that are all worth trying. With a total of more than 20 water rides that are ready to provide exciting experiences for water ride challenge lovers. Bendulan, Blaster Warrior, Jungle Tree, Great Wall are just a few of the dozens of other rides that can be played. Of course, all of them are supported by complete facilities such as Gazebo, Family Gazebo, Vip Court, etc. All of them are there to add to the comfort of every visitor who will play in this Lumpia City Waterpark.

Jatibarang Reservoir is a reservoir in the city of Semarang. The construction of this reservoir was completed after about four years of construction and began the process of filling with water on May 5, 2014 to coincide with the 22nd World Water Day by the Minister of Public Works Djoko Kirmanto together with the Governor of Central Java Ganjar Pranowo and the Head of the Pemali River Basin Center Juwana Imam Santoso. \nThe Jatibarang Reservoir officially began operating on May 11 2015. The inauguration was carried out by the Director General of Water Resources of the Ministry of Public Works and Public Housing, Mudjiadi to coincide with the commemoration of the 23rd World Water Day at the Central Java Provincial Level. \nThe Jatibarang Reservoir has a capacity of 20, 4 million cubic meters . In addition to overcoming the problem of flooding, it has also become one of Semarang's tourist destinations because in the middle of this reservoir there is a small island in which there is another tourist object, namely Goa Kreo.

Tirto Argo Siwarak Swimming Pool, is a swimming pool located in Ungaran. Its close proximity to the city of Semarang makes this tourist spot quite popular. In fact, it is not uncommon for tourists from Semarang and its surroundings to visit. Comes with a swimming pool and a simple recreation park, it is actually the main attraction. Evidently, visitors who come never recede. In fact, there are always visitors and it is crowded during the holidays.

Tourism in the Mount Kelir area has indeed started to become popular since the beginning of 2021 and tourists often flock there to quell curiosity about this new destination. Mount Kelir has a height of more than 2000 meters above sea level and the Kelir Slope tour is above an altitude reaching 1384 meters above sea level and 700 meters above sea level. From this height, you can see almost the entire area of Ambarawa city and a small part of the southern Semarang area. The viewing post tour of the Kelir Slope can indeed be said to be higher than other viewing post tourist spots in Central Java.

Kampoeng Rawa (also known as Kampung Rawa) is a tourist attraction in Ambarawa, Central Java, which is located in the green belt around Lake Rawa Pening. Opened in August 2012, it is owned and operated by twelve groups of farmers and fishermen funded by the Artha Prima Credit Union. The complex is intended to influence the welfare of farmers and serve the local besides promoting the ecology of the lake in the region. Facilities include a floating restaurant, pavilion, craft center, fishing spot and dock. On holidays, this place is visited by hundreds of visitors. The complex is disputed over licensing because it was built in a green belt and its possible ecological impact.

The Palagan Ambarawa Monument is a monument located in Ambarawa, Semarang Regency. Allied forces pushed out of Magelang held a retreat to Ambarawa, and TKR troops led by Colonel Soedirman succeeded in destroying the Allies on December 15, 1945, which is now commemorated as Infantry Day. The Palagan Ambarawa Monument was built in 1973 and inaugurated on December 15, 1974 by the President Suharto. A brief description of the history of the battle can be seen in the reliefs made on the walls of the Palagan Ambarawa Monument. In this monument you can find relics of the Japanese and Dutch governments. You can see the uniforms of Japanese and Dutch soldiers, weapons of war, Indonesian army uniforms, and other historical items. For a rather large size, you can find several ancient tanks, personnel transport vehicles and cannons used in the battle. The most interesting thing is that you can find a Dutch Mustang plane that was successfully shot down into Rawa Pening

Fort Pendem Cilacap (Dutch: Kustbatterij op de Landtong te Cilacap), is a Dutch heritage fort on the coast of Teluk Penyu, Cilacap district, Central Java, which was built in 1861. This building was a former defense headquarters for the Dutch East Indies army which was built in an area of 6 .5 hectares in stages over 18 years, from 1861 to 1879. Fort Pendem was once covered with coastal land and was neglected. This fort was later discovered and excavated by the Cilacap government began in 1986. Currently, the Cilacap Regency government has made this fort a historical tourist spot

tourist facility that is managed in a modern way, to create the enjoyment of traveling as desired by young people. But still one with the environment, with the beauty of nature. Without doing harm to nature. This tourist facility is the Eling Bening tour in the Ngrawan hills. Eling Bening is actually a restaurant that carries the concept of family tourism. Eling Bening offers very beautiful natural scenery with the main view of Rawa Pening. This beauty is further enhanced by the background of Mount Merbabu, Andong and Telomoyo, which can be seen standing proudly.

Maria Kerep Cave (Ambarawa Maria Kerep Cave, abbreviated as GMKA), is a place of pilgrimage located on Student Army Road, Panjang Village, Ambarawa. This place is quite a good place to pray, pilgrimage, and freshen up. The distance is about 500 m from the Ambarawa Terminal. Because it is far from the highway, this area is quite quiet. From this place you can see views of Mount Telomoyo, Mount Merbabu, and Lake Rawa Pening. Maria Kerep Cave has facilities for pilgrims, including Way of the Cross, Lesehan Prayer Place, Church, and a garden.

The Ambarawa Railway Museum (English: Indonesian Railway Museum, Ambarawa) is a train station that has been converted into a museum and is the first railway museum in Indonesia. This museum has a collection of trains that once triumphed in their time. This museum is administratively located in Panjang Village, Ambarawa, Semarang. The museum, which is located at an altitude of +474.40 meters, is included in the Operational Area IV of Semarang and is managed by PT Kereta Api Indonesia's Center for Preservation and Architectural Design in collaboration with the Central Java Provincial Government.

It is undeniable that the Kayon Getasan Pine Forest near Salatiga is indeed a beautiful tourist spot and spoils the eye. Visitors will be presented with a neat and beautiful array of pine forests. This row of trees is indeed alluring and of course the Kayon Pine Forest or called the Kali Pasang Pine Forest can be an alternative for family tourism. Apart from being quite complete there, the walks in the forest are also cast. Thus, of course, it will spoil visitors more when exploring this tourist area.

Kota Lama Semarang (Javanese: ˆ? ˆ??ˆ??ƒ??ˆ?ˆ??ƒ??ˆ?ñˆ?¬ˆ??ˆ?®ˆ? , translit. Kutha Lama Semarang) is an area in Semarang which became the center of trade in the 19-20 century. At that time, to protect the people and their territory, a fort was built in that area, which was named the Vijhoek fort. To speed up the transportation route between the three gates in the fort, transportation roads were made, with the main road being named: Heeren Straat. Currently named Jl. Let Jen Suprapto. One of the locations of the fort gates that exist today is the Berok Bridge, which is called De Zuider Por. The Old Town area of Semarang is also called Outstadt. The area of this area is about 31 hectares. Judging from the geographical conditions, it appears that this area is separated from the surrounding area, so that it looks like a separate city with the nickname "Little Netherland". The Old Town area of Semarang is a silent witness to the history of Indonesia during the Dutch colonial period for more than 2 centuries, and is located side by side with the economic area. In this place there are about 50 ancient buildings that are still standing firmly and have a history of Colonialism in Semarang. In general, the character of the buildings in this area follows those of the European continent around the 1700s. This can be seen from the distinctive building details and ornaments that are identical to the European style. Such as the size of the doors and windows that are extraordinarily large, the use of colored glass, the unique shape of the roof, to the presence of basements. Like other cities under Dutch colonial rule, a fort was also built as a military center. This fort is pentagonal in shape and was first built on the west side of the old city of Semarang today. This fort has only one gate on its south side and five watchtowers. Each tower is named: Zeeland, Amsterdam, Utrecht, Raamsdonk and Bunschoten. The Dutch government moved Chinese settlements in 1731 near Dutch settlements, to facilitate monitoring of all Chinese activities. Therefore, Benteng is not only a military center, but also a watchtower for all activities of the Chinese people. It is planned that the Old City of Semarang will be proposed by the UNESCO World Heritage Site.

The establishment of the Semarang Chinatown was inseparable from the Chinatown commotion in Batavia (former Jakarta) in 1740. At that time, the Chinese people rebelled against the Dutch authorities. In the aftermath of the tragedy, many residents of Chinese descent fled along the north coast of Java until they finally arrived in Semarang. Until 1743, the rebellion was still going on until finally it was completely stopped by the Dutch army. The colonial government then decided to gather Chinese citizens in one location. After occupying the Simongan area near the Sam Poo Kong Temple, they were then moved to the Semarang River until finally it became known as the Chinatown area until now.

La Kana Chapel offers a new concept of standing party, indulge your taste buds with a special live cooking menu, fresh dishes a la minute on your plate. This is the Royal Wedding Venue in the Most Beautiful Place on the Mountain. For those of you who want a touch of luxury and glamor for outdoor and indoor parties. La Cana Chapel can accommodate up to 48 people in the chapel and 500 more in the courtyard. And the ballroom can accommodate 1000 people

This bridge is located in Tuntang, Kab. Semarang, Central Java. close to swamp pening and Tuntang River. If you are used to going back and forth from Salatiga-Semarang, you must be familiar with the Tuntang Bridge. So... the Tuntang River is right under the Tuntang Bridge which empties into Rawa Pening. For visitors who like to take pictures, Blue Bridge Tourism has some of the best photo spots, one of which is in the middle of the bridge. If lucky, visitors will also see a steam train passing in front of the Blue Bridge Tour. From the top of the bridge visitors can also see Mount Ungaran, Mount Temoloyo and also Mount Merbabu.

Semarang has a tour at a height called Goa Rong. The existence of this tourist area shows that Semarang is not only synonymous with Lawang Sewu or the Old City. Even though it is called Goa Rong, the place that stands out here is not the cave itself. But an altitude area with amazing views. While in this tourist attraction, the cave is only a narrow passage and does not allow humans to enter. But on the contrary, the view presented from the top of the hill is so amazing. Tourists can spend time taking pictures, enjoying the scenery, or culinary at the cafe. In fact, outbound facilities are also available.

Al-Mabrur Grand Mosque is located on Jln. Ahmad Yani, Sidomulyo Village, Ungaran Tibur District, Semarang Regency, Central Java Province. This mosque is also the Grand Mosque for Semarang Regency, the capital of Central Java Province. The Al-Mabrur Grand Mosque was also known previously as the Mosque of the Indonesian Hajj Brotherhood Association (IPHI). The construction of this mosque began in 2010 with the establishment taking up an area of 3,200 square meters, with a building area of around 1,550 square meters. Because it was intended to become the Great Mosque of Semarang City, this mosque building was erected right facing Semarang City Square, or better known as "Asmara Square" and opposite the Semarang Regent's Office House.

Tugu Muda ("Youth Monument" Indonesian) is a stone monument in Semarang, Java commemorating the struggle for independence by Indonesian youth. It was dedicated by President Sukarno on 20 May 1953 to commemorate the five days of continuous fighting between the youth of Semarang and a Japanese battalion led by Major Kido from 14-19 October 1945. Japanese troops expelled the Dutch from Indonesia as "the older brother of Asia"; however, the Japanese were more ruthless towards dissenters than their Dutch counterparts. The stone monument consists of a foundation, body and head. One side of the monument is made in relief, with an ornamental pond and garden surrounding it.

Kampoeng Kopi Banaran, an agro-tourism coffee plantation in Semarang Regency. This tourist spot has an area of 462 hectares, some of which are used as resorts and tourist attractions. The location is in the Getas Afdeling Assinan Coffee Plantation Area, precisely Jl. Raya Semarang ? Solo Km. 35. The location of Kampoeng Kopi Banaran which is at an altitude of 480 ? 600m above sea level makes the air temperature there cool between 23?§C ? 27?§C. So it's really suitable for vacations looking for cold and fresh air with beautiful views. Get rid of the bustle of the big city, in the middle of a beautiful plantation.

Tabanas Park is a park located on the Gombel Rise, Semarang. From Tabanas Park, Semarang, visitors can see the landscape of the city of Semarang, making Tabanas Park one of the attractions to visit. Around the Tabanas Park, Semarang, there are cafes, restaurants, and hotels, which add to the beauty and become a special attraction for the Tabanas Park, Semarang. Tabanas Park also has the name Gardu Pandang Gombel Semarang, although Semarang residents themselves know this park better by the name Tabanas Park.

It is undeniable that Kampung Jawi Gunungpati Semarang has indeed gone viral and has even been visited by many people. Even though this culinary tour started in a small village, now it has been visited by many local residents and outside the city. Even now, fame often adorns social media pages. When visiting Kampung Jawi Gunungpati, you can feel the old village atmosphere. Apart from that, the nuances of the night are also peaceful and night plus the lighting is dim, because they use Sentir lamps (oil lamps). So it's really cool to hang out for a long time.

Semarang Batik Village is one of the unique and interesting villages in the city of Semarang which has always been associated with Semarang batik since ancient times until now. Semarang Batik Village is located around the Bubagan area, Semarang. Semarang Batik Village in history from the 1970s to the 1980s, at that time it was completely dead, there was no batik activity. It was only later in 2005 that there were activities, this took place because there was an assumption "why is the name Kampung Batik Semarang". However, how come no one is making batik, so activities such as batik training are often encouraged, this is aimed at facilitating and revitalizing Semarang Batik Village. At that time it was famous for its Krajan Batik, Gedong Batik, Central Batik, Malang Batik, Kubur Sari Batik and Kandang Wedus Batik which were famous for their own motifs. However, it is a shame that this motif was not recorded visually, and this is actually a treasure trove that has not been visually discovered until now in these batik motifs.

Located on the northern slope of Mount Ungaran, there is an exotic waterfall with a green swimming pool surrounded by trees and cool mountain air. The name of the location is Semirang Waterfall or also called Semirang Waterfall. And the people of Semarang call it Curug Semarang. Because of the beauty of this tourist location, tourists often visit it on weekdays, especially when the holidays arrive. Semirang Waterfall or Semirang Waterfall is located in a protected forest area with an area of 10 hectares under the management of Perum Perhutani. This waterfall has a height of about 45 meters. The distance between the parking location and the location of the waterfall is about 500 meters. And during the trip, visitors will be presented with beautiful natural scenery with very cool fresh air.

Goa Kreo Semarang, which is located in the capital of Central Java, is a hit among netizens. No wonder if the weather is sunny, the queue to get there is so snaking. Even though there is no public transportation to get there, it doesn't stop tourists' curiosity. This cave is formed naturally, what distinguishes this cave from other caves is its location. its location is in the middle of the jatibarang reservoir, a dam that dams the Kreo River.

Natural attractions are indeed very suitable to visit, especially on weekends. Plus, the location of the tourist attraction is not too far from the city center. Like the Watu Gunung tourist attraction in Ungaran, Semarang City. Visiting natural attractions can make the mind fresh. Moreover, this tourist attraction offers captivating natural and water attractions. In addition, it is also combined with a distinctive Javanese traditional nuance. Previously, the Watu Gunung area was not a tourist attraction. Only the land is overgrown with dense nutmeg and clove trees. Unfortunately, the area is arid and difficult to get water. Then, in 2004 the owner took the initiative to build a private villa. And over time, a tourist attraction was created that was open to the public. While maintaining the joglo building as its trademark.

In Indonesia, Brown Canyon is a former mining land in Meteseh, Tembalang, Semarang. This location is one of the popular locations (not a tourist spot) in Semarang and is considered similar to the Grand Canyon in the United States. This similarity lies in the hills that turn into steep cliffs.

Place_Name: Durian Gardens and Tourism Education Watu Simbar
Description: Please note, this simbar stone is a tourist location that offers education from various types of durian trees. Even though it seems ordinary, that is what makes this place unique. If someone comes here, that person will be able to learn many things about the durian tree. Apart from being able to learn various things about the durian tree, of course visitors can also buy the durian that is there.

In the Setiya Aji Flower Farm flower garden, we can see the colorful chrysanthemum flowers which look very beautiful. Besides that, its location in the highlands makes the air in the Bandungan flower garden feel quite fresh. In an instant, the Setiya Aji Flower Farm Bandungan flower garden attracted the attention of tourists, especially young people who were curious to see the beauty of the flowers in this Semarang tourist spot. Now Setiya Aji Flower Farm is one of the favorite tourist attractions in Bandungan that must be visited, especially for tourists who are looking for romantic attractions in Semarang Regency besides Gedong Songo.

Surabaya Mangrove Tourism Forest is a tour that combines recreational and educational tourism. In an area of approximately 200 hectares, various mangrove plants are planted. This tourist location is well managed by the Surabaya City government. So that this tour attracts visitors because it is neat and clean. The Submarine Monument, or abbreviated as Monkasel, is a submarine museum located in Embong Kaliasin, Genteng, Surabaya. Located in the city center, this monument is actually a KRI Pasopati 410 submarine, one of the Republic of Indonesia Navy fleets made by the Soviet Union in 1952. This submarine was involved in the Battle of the Aru Sea to liberate West Irian from Dutch occupation. brought ashore and made into a monument to commemorate the bravery of Indonesian heroes. Monkasel is on Jalan Pemuda, right next to Plaza Surabaya. In addition to the interior of the submarine, there is also a film showing about the process of the war that occurred in the Aru Sea. If you want to visit this tourist spot, you will be accompanied by a local guide who is there. \nThere is a unique story behind the presence of this Submarine monument. One night Pak Drajat Budiyanto, who is a former KKM KRI Pasopati 410 (made in Russia) and also a former KKM KRI Cakra 401 (made in West Germany), dreamed that he was ordered by the KSAL at that time to take this submarine to sail Kali Mas. It turned out that the dream had come true. He was assigned to display the submarine beside Surabaya Plaza. You do this by cutting the submarine into several parts, then transporting it ashore, and reassembling and reconnecting it to become a complete submarine.

Kenjeran Park is one of the modern tourist attractions in Surabaya. This tourist spot is located right on Jalan Sukolilo, Sukolilo Baru Village, Bulak District, Surabaya, East Java. Kenjeran Park consists of several tourist areas that visitors can choose from. For those who bring children and like swimming, visitors can visit Atlantis Land Kenjeran. Then, visitors can also visit several iconic places from Kenjeran Park. One of them is the Tian Ti Pagoda. The Tian Ti Pagoda has a design inspired by the Tian Tan Pagoda in Beijing, China. However, the Tian Ti Pagoda consists of three floors with a diameter of 60 meters and a height of 58 meters. Another iconic place is the 4 Faced Buddha Statue. The Buddha statue is 36 meters high. Another interesting place that visitors can visit is the Sanggar Agung Temple. In this pagoda, visitors can see a statue of the Goddess Kwan Im and a pair of red and golden dragons that directly face the beach.

Surabaya Zoo (KBS) (Arekan Dialect: Suroboyo Zoo) is one of the most popular zoos in Indonesia and is located in Surabaya. KBS is the most complete zoo in Southeast Asia, in which there are more than 981 different animal species consisting of more than 2,806 animals. The Cheng Hoo Mosque in Surabaya is a Chinese Muslim-style mosque located on Jalan Gading, Ketabang, Genteng, Surabaya or 1,000 m north of the Surabaya City Hall Building. This mosque was founded on the initiative of the elders, advisors, PITI administrators, and administrators of the East Java Muhammad Cheng Ho Indonesia Haji Foundation as well as Chinese community leaders in Surabaya. The construction of this mosque began with the laying of the first stone on 15 October 2001 to coincide with the Isra' Mi'raj of the Prophet Muhammad SAW. While the construction was only carried out on March 10, 2002 and was inaugurated on October 13, 2002. The Cheng Ho Mosque, or also known as the Muhammad Cheng Ho Mosque in Surabaya, is a mosque building that resembles a temple (a place of worship for Tri Dharma followers). This building is located in the area of the PITI (Islamic Tauhid Imam Pembina) multi-purpose building complex in East Java, Jalan Gading No.2 (Behind the Kusuma Bangsa Heroes Cemetery), Surabaya. This mosque is dominated by red, green and yellow colors. The ornaments have a strong old Chinese feel. The entrance resembles the shape of a pagoda, there are also reliefs of dragons and lion statues made of wax with the word Allah in Arabic letters at the top of the pagoda. On the left side of the building there is a drum as a complement to the mosque building. Apart from Surabaya in Palembang there is also a similar mosque with the name Cheng Ho Palembang Mosque or Al Islam Muhammad Cheng Hoo Sriwijaya Mosque Palembang. The name of this mosque is a form of respect for Cheng Ho, an admiral from China who is Muslim. In his travels in the Southeast Asian region, Cheng Ho not only traded and made friends, but also spread Islam.

The Al Akbar National Mosque (or commonly called the Great Mosque of Surabaya) is the second largest mosque in Indonesia, located in the city of Surabaya, East Java after the Istiqlal Mosque in Jakarta. The position of this mosque is in the Pagesangan Village area, Jambangan District, Surabaya and right next to the Surabaya-Gempol Toll Road. An easy-to-see feature is the large dome accompanied by 4 small blue domes. It also has a tower that is 99 meters high. The Surabaya Al-Akbar National Mosque was built on August 4, 1995, on the idea of the Mayor of Surabaya at that time, H. Soenarto Soemoprawiro. The construction of this mosque was marked by the laying of the first stone by Indonesian Vice President Try Sutrisno. However, due to the monetary crisis, the construction was stopped temporarily. In 1999, this mosque was rebuilt and completed in 2001. On November 10, 2000, this mosque was inaugurated by the President of the Republic of Indonesia KH. Abdurrahman Wahid.

Place_Name: Museum TNI AL Loka Jala Crana
Description: The Loka Jala Crana Museum was founded on September 19, 1969 by Mrs. R. Mulyadi, the wife of the commander of the Navy, Admiral R. Moeljadi, under the name of the Indonesian Military Academy Museum. In 1973, on July 10, 1973 to be exact, its status was upgraded to become the Indonesian Navy Museum. Then on October 6, 1979 the name changed again to the Loka Jala Crana Navy Museum. Loka jala Crana means a place to store, perpetuate and present equipment or facilities used by the Indonesian Navy. Inside this museum there are several collections of Navy fighting equipment, besides that there is also a collection in the form of a planetarium and astronavigation. This museum presents and saves historic objects that have been owned and used by soldiers of the Indonesian Navy since the time of the physical revolution until now, including various types of warship cannons, planes, helicopters, field artillery, replica KRI Dewaruci . There are also other historical objects such as the "HRMS De Zeven Provencien" ship cannon.

The Red Bridge is a historical monument in Surabaya, East Java, which has been left as it is: as a bridge. The bridge, which became one of the titles of Gesang's songs, during the VOC era was considered important because it was the most vital means of transportation past Kalimas to the Surabaya Residency Building, which no longer has a trace. The Red Bridge area is a commercial area that began to develop as a result of the Agreement Paku Buwono II of Mataram with the VOC on November 11, 1743. Under this agreement, part of the north coast, including Surabaya, was handed over to the VOC. Since then Surabaya was completely under Dutch rule. Now, its position as a trade center continues. Around the bridge there are economic indicators, including one of which is Plaza Jembatan Merah. The physical changes occurred around the 1890s, when the fence with the river was changed from wood to iron. Now the condition of the bridge that connects Jalan Rajawali and Jalan Kembang Jepun on the north side of Surabaya is almost exactly the same as the other bridges. The difference is only red.

Museum Bank Indonesia (Indonesian: Museum Bank Indonesia) is a bank museum located in Surabaya, Indonesia. Officially established by Bank Indonesia and opened on 27 January 2012 after restoration. This museum occupies a building that was formerly called De Javasche Bank, the central bank of the Dutch East Indies. After Indonesian Independence this building continued to function as the branch office of Bank Indonesia in Surabaya until 1973. The museum is closed on Mondays and national holidays. There is no entry fee.

The area, which is nicknamed Kampung Keraton, consists of four alleys. This alley is on average narrow, 2 to 3 meters wide. It is so narrow that motorcyclists sometimes get out of their vehicles and have to walk. Meanwhile, the length of the road is about 200 meters. Indeed, there are not many remains of this Surabaya Palace. What is visible now is the remains of the Dutch colonial heritage. Kampung Keraton is currently one of the busiest trading areas in Surabaya, especially on Jalan Kramat Gantung. All kinds of household needs are sold on this street.

Sanggar Agung Temple or Hong San Tang Temple is a temple in the city of Surabaya. The address is at Jalan Sukolilo Number 100, Pantai Ria Kenjeran, Surabaya. This temple, apart from being a place of worship for adherents of the Tridharma, is also a tourist destination for tourists. This pagoda opened in 1999. The distinctive feature of this pagoda is a 20 meter high statue of Kwan Im which is located by the sea. This temple is dedicated to Nan Hai Guan Shi Yin Pu Sa or South Sea Kwan Im Bodhisattva. This statue was built after an employee of Sanggar Agung saw a woman in a white robe walking on the water when she was closing the Pagoda at night. The sighting is believed to be the appearance of Kwan Im himself. Another icon from Sanggar Agung is a giant gold-plated Phra Phrom statue.

The Surabaya Ten November Museum is one of the museums located in the city of Surabaya, built in 1945. This museum was built with the aim of studying and deepening the events of the 1945 Ten November Battle. The Ten November Museum is located at Jalan Pahlawan, Surabaya.

Tugu Pahlawan (Indonesian: Tugu Pahlawan) is a monument in Surabaya, Indonesia. It is the main emblem of the city which is dedicated to the people who died in the Battle of Surabaya on 10 November 1945. The 10 November Museum is located under the monument. This monument has a height of 41.15 meters and is in the shape of a phallus. Built to commemorate the events of 10 November 1945 in the Battle of Surabaya. It is the place every November 10 to commemorate the events of 1945, when many heroes died in the war for independence. The laying of the first stone was led by Soekarno, the first President of Indonesia, accompanied by the Mayor of Surabaya, Doel Arnowo on 10 November 1951. It was inaugurated a year later, also by Soekarno, on 10 November 1952 witnessed by the Mayor of Surabaya, R. Moestadjab Soemowidigdo. The 10 November Museum was built to explain the meaning behind the Heroes Monument. The building consists of 2 floors, with exhibitions that symbolize the fighting spirit of the people of Surabaya. There is an auditorium on the first floor. The museum contains reproductions of documentary photographs, and there is a diorama which presents eight events that occurred around the clashes of 10 November 1945.

Currently the Surabaya Siola Museum is transformed into a unique and interesting historical tourist destination to visit. Not only presenting stories of the past displayed in various forms, the Surabaya Siola Museum is also a target spot for photo hunting. For visitors who want to visit the Surabaya Siola Museum, they do not have to pay an entrance ticket, which is free. Anyone can enter the Surabaya Siola Museum, because this place is open to all groups, from children to adults. There doesn't seem to be anything wrong with Manjajal Museum Surabaya as your weekend tourist destination. Museum of Health Dr. Adhyatma, MPH is a health museum that was initiated by the Government of Indonesia through the Ministry of Health on December 16, 2003. The Health Museum, Research and Development Center for Health Services and Technology (PUSLITBANG YANTEKKES) was inaugurated by the Minister of Health on September 14, 2004, so it was named the Dr. Health Museum. Adhyatma, MPH. Health Museum Dr. Adhyatma, MPH, located at Jl. Indrapura 17 Surabaya, East Java.

The Jalesveva Jayamahe Monument or Monjaya is a monument located in the city of Surabaya, East Java. This monument depicts the figure of a TNI Navy officer dressed in Ceremonial Uniform (PDU) complete with a sword of honor looking out to sea, as if ready to challenge the waves and storms at sea, as well as what he wants to show that the Indonesian navy is ready to triumph. The statue stands on top of the building and reaches 30.6 meters high. The Jalesveva Jayamahe Monument depicts the nation's next generation who are confident and optimistic about achieving the ideals of the Indonesian nation. The Jalesveva Jayamahe Monument is also in accordance with the Jalesveva Jayamahe naval motto which means, In the Sea We Glory. This monument was built in 1993 by the Chief of Staff of the Indonesian Maritime Navy which was then continued by Admiral TNI Muhamad Arifin and designed by I Nyoman Nuarta. Apart from being a monument, this building also functions as a lighthouse for ships in the surrounding sea.

The statue of Sura and Baya (Javanese: Statue of Suro lan Boyo) is a statue which is the symbol of the city of Surabaya. This statue is in front of the Surabaya Zoo. This statue consists of these two animals that inspired the name of the city of Surabaya: ikan sura (shark) and baya (crocodile).

Surabaya Ria Kenjeran Beach tourism object is one of the tourist destinations when visiting the city of Surabaya. This beach has quite complete facilities, such as a playground for children called Kya Kya Seaside, there is also the Tuan Ti Pagoda, a wooden bridge with a gazebo for relaxing and taking photos. There is also a waterpark and children's play area around this beach. Waterpark Kenjeran Surabaya is a family tour with water games and swimming sports. There are various interesting rides for families and children. Surabaya as Resort Gemeente (Haminte) was officially established on April 1, 1906. Previously, Surabaya was part of the residency of the Haminte Government, run by the Haminte Council, which was chaired by the assistant resident as Regional Head. In 1916, the first Mayor of Surabaya was appointed, A. Meyroos who served until 1921. It was only after the second mayor, GJ DIJKERMAN, was elected, that plans to build the City Hall building were realized. 
The main City Hall building in Taman Surya in the Ketabang area began construction in 1923 and was occupied in 1927. The architect namely C. Citroen and its implementation HV Hollandsche Beton Mij. The total cost, including fittings and other expenses, cost about 1000 guilders.

Size of the main building: 102 m long and 19 m wide. The construction consists of embedded reinforced concrete piles, while the walls are filled with brick and cement. The roof was made of iron frame and covered with shingles. Later this roof was replaced with tiles. After the Republic of Indonesia was proclaimed, Radjamin Nasution was installed as Mayor of the Big City of Surabaya. Based on Presidential Decree No. 1959. 16 then the mayor was appointed as the Regional Head of Surabaya City. In 1965 the Municipality of Surabaya officially became a Municipality.

Located on the corner of Ria Kenjeran Beach, this Four Way Buddha Statue is often used by local youths as a place to hang out and gather. It was built starting in 2003 and has a land area of about 1.5 hectares and measures 9 ? 9 meters, making it spend around IDR 4 billion in its manufacture. And this statue is even more magnificent because it is covered in pure gold imported directly from Thailand. This building is surrounded by 4 pillars, namely green pillars and golden pillars. The four faces on this statue depict the four good qualities of the Buddha, namely compassion, generosity, justice and meditation. Apart from seeing this Buddha statue, if you visit here you will see several elephant statues around this Buddha statue. And interestingly, this statue is considered by MURI as the tallest statue in Indonesia.

The Sharp Bamboo Monument is a Surabaya tourism icon related to the historical site of the nation's struggle. This monument consists of 5 pillars and has unequal height and is shaped like sharp bamboo. Unfortunately, there is no precise estimate of the height of each pillar. At certain times, there will be water flowing out of the spiky bamboo, like a fountain. In addition, this monument is surrounded by a small garden full of various ornamental plants. This Sharp Bamboo Monument is located in the heart of Surabaya, in the middle of the busy Panglima Sudirman traffic. Visitors who come to Surabaya will immediately recognize the existence of this monument when they cross it. This monument is also close to the Surabaya Zoo, Tunjungan Plaza, Surabaya Plaza and the Surabaya Heroes Monument.

House of Sampoerna is a tobacco museum and Sampoerna's headquarters located in Surabaya. The architectural style of the main building which is influenced by the Dutch colonial style was built in 1862 and is now a historical site. Previously used as an orphanage run by the Dutch, it was purchased in 1932 by Liem Seeng Teeƒ?? Sampoernaƒ?? founder with the aim of being used as Sampoerna's first major cigarette production facility.

Since it was inaugurated in December 2017, Atlantis Land Kenjeran Surabaya has been successful in bringing in many visitors. This water tourism park is the largest water park in the city of Surabaya. The location is in the same area as Kenjeran Park, or familiarly called Ken Park. Precisely on Jalan Pantai Ria Kenjeran, Sukolilo Baru, Bulak, Surabaya, East Java. This water tourism park has an area of about 15 hectares with an original design belonging to an Australian architect. The theme taken for this water tourism park is an underwater palace. With this theme, the entrance gate of Atlantis Land Kenjeran Surabaya has a blue main building wall. The main wall is decorated with stripes resembling white waves. The roof is yellow-brown and towering like a palace. On both sides of the main building, there are brown-walled buildings with wooden split ornaments. This building gives the impression of an unfinished cruise ship. A yellow Neptune statue can also be seen adorning one corner of the garden wall. The decorations in Atlantis Land Kenjeran will give the atmosphere like being in a castle.

The People's Entertainment Park or THR is certainly no stranger to the people of Surabaya. This park is located behind the Surabaya Youth Park (TRS) and also behind the Hi-Tech Mall. THR is usually used for regional art performances. This park has become an icon of Surabaya because of its quite interesting history.

Mundu Park is a park or green open space, especially for residents of the city of Surabaya, this park is located on Jl. Tambaksari or across from the Ten November Tambaksari Stadium, Surabaya. Mundu Park was built to occupy an area of 4,800 square meters and its construction was inaugurated on July 10, 2010. This beautiful park has various facilities that can be enjoyed and used by Surabaya residents or anyone who visits this park, including a playground facility for children,

The Mpu Tantular State Museum is a state museum located in the Buduran sub-district, Sidoarjo, East Java. Initially, this museum was named Stedelijk Historisch Museum Soerabaia, founded by Godfried von Faber in 1933 and inaugurated on July 25, 1937. Currently, this museum is managed by the Technical Implementation Unit at the Ministry of Culture and Tourism.

Bungkul Park is a city tourism park located in the center of Surabaya, precisely on Jalan Raya Darmo. This park stands in an area of 900 square meters. Equipped with various supporting facilities, such as an amphitheater with a diameter of 33 meters, jogging track, skateboard area, children's playground, fountain and food court. Apart from that, this park is also equipped with wireless internet access which is open to the public so that anyone can access the internet while in this park. Its location in the heart of Surabaya City makes this park not only function as a green area, but also as a popular tourist destination in Surabaya.

There is also a dancing fountain in the Kenjeran Bridge area, Surabaya. This fountain was made simultaneously with the construction of the Kenjeran Bridge, which was inaugurated on July 9, 2016. Since the inauguration of the fountain and bridge that stretches over the sea with a length of 800 meters, it has become a tourist destination for residents of Surabaya and its surroundings. A beautiful dancing fountain cannot be separated from the components that work in it, such as a nozzle where water comes out, from this nozzle the water jets can change. The water that comes out is pushed by a fountain pump that pushes it from a low place to a higher place. Choosing the right lamp will add to the quality of the lighting, it is better to use underwater led or waterproof led because these lights are waterproof. Of course it will add to the appearance of a dancing fountain more alluring.

Flora Park is one of the city parks in Surabaya which is a public facility of the local municipal government. So this place was deliberately made to be enjoyed by the general public. Because this park is a public facility established by the Surabaya City Government, anyone who wants to take advantage of this city park does not need to pay an entrance ticket or it is free.

Place_Name: Church of the Immaculate Virgin Mary Surabaya
Description: The Catholic Church of the Nativity of the Virgin Mary is one of the old churches in the city of Surabaya, East Java, Indonesia. Located on Jalan Kepanjen, Surabaya, this religious building is adjacent to the Surabaya Frateran Catholic High School building.
